00:40.375 --> 00:44.209
All too often

00:44.278 --> 00:47.805
I set my life aside

00:49.317 --> 00:52.445
All too often

00:52.520 --> 00:56.854
My dreams went sailing by

00:58.393 --> 01:01.123
A chance of freedom

01:02.230 --> 01:05.221
A chance of faith

01:06.768 --> 01:10.295
A chance I'll take

01:10.371 --> 01:19.075
Knowing it all will disappear

01:19.147 --> 01:24.483
It ain't anywhere but here

01:27.455 --> 01:31.221
All too often

01:31.292 --> 01:34.750
The dreams I dreamed have died

01:36.330 --> 01:39.595
All too often...

01:39.667 --> 01:42.830
My mother made
an amazing amount of noise

01:42.904 --> 01:44.838
when she ate her food.

01:44.906 --> 01:49.240
It was as if she was trying to
taste the entire world.

01:49.310 --> 01:52.177
Sometimes I just couldn't stand her.

01:53.848 --> 01:55.577
Sometimes I hated her.

01:56.951 --> 02:00.182
Sometimes I thought
she was ruining my life.

02:00.254 --> 02:04.350
What kept me going was knowing
that one day I would leave her.

02:05.726 --> 02:11.221
I'll find it anywhere but here

02:17.371 --> 02:20.169
Come on, baby, surfin' safari

02:20.241 --> 02:29.340
Yeah, I'm gonna take you
surfin' safari

02:29.417 --> 02:30.941
Let's go surfin' now

02:31.018 --> 02:32.508
Everybody's learnin' how

02:32.587 --> 02:34.350
Come on a safari with me

02:34.422 --> 02:35.354
Ba la la la la la la

02:36.657 --> 02:37.851
I hate this song.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.586
I love this song.
It's the Beach Boys.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.389
I hate the Beach Boys.

02:41.462 --> 02:42.724
Honey, how can you
hate the Beach Boys?

02:42.797 --> 02:43.729
Nobody hates the Beach Boys.

02:43.798 --> 02:45.095
They're too happy and sunny.

02:45.166 --> 02:47.498
Well, you're gonna have to learn
to like happy and sunny,

02:47.568 --> 02:50.230
because that's what
California's all about.

02:51.939 --> 02:55.466
Oh, next stop, Salt Lake City. Yes!

02:55.543 --> 02:58.239
Salt Lake City, Utah.
The capital, right?

02:58.312 --> 02:59.301
I don't care.

02:59.380 --> 03:00.506
Oh, yes, you do care.

03:00.581 --> 03:01.980
Come on, don't mumble.
You care.

03:02.049 --> 03:03.880
You're very good at capitals.

03:03.951 --> 03:05.976
Idaho.

03:06.053 --> 03:07.987
Come on, Pooh Bear, Idaho.

03:08.055 --> 03:09.079
Stop calling me Pooh Bear.

03:09.157 --> 03:11.557
But you are my little Pooh Bear.
Come on.

03:11.626 --> 03:13.719
Come on. Idaho.

03:13.794 --> 03:15.762
Boise!
I don't want to play.

03:15.830 --> 03:16.854
Ok, now you do one for me.

03:16.931 --> 03:18.330
A really hard one.

03:18.399 --> 03:20.765
I said I don't want to play.

03:22.403 --> 03:23.335
Oregon.

03:23.404 --> 03:24.735
Portland. Too easy.

03:24.805 --> 03:25.737
Salem.

03:25.806 --> 03:27.171
It's Salem?

03:27.241 --> 03:29.175
I don't want to do this anymore.

03:29.243 --> 03:32.076
I don't want to be in Utah.

03:32.146 --> 03:37.413
2,000 miles between us and Bay City. Ok.

03:37.485 --> 03:39.544
I want to be back in Bay City.

03:39.620 --> 03:40.746
This is like being kidnapped.

03:40.821 --> 03:42.049
You don't understand that, do you?

03:42.123 --> 03:43.647
I wish somebody had kidnapped me

03:43.724 --> 03:44.918
when I was your age.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.254
So do I.

04:01.676 --> 04:05.009
Grandma always said
that my mom was a strange child.

04:11.719 --> 04:14.950
Oh, this is absolutely moribound.

04:15.022 --> 04:16.579
Gwen Purvis has cancer.

04:16.656 --> 04:17.988
That's worse.

04:18.059 --> 04:19.185
I didn't give it to her.

04:20.528 --> 04:22.359
You didn't give it to her.

04:22.430 --> 04:24.398
That's funny, Aunt Adele.

04:24.465 --> 04:25.659
You're gonna die
one day, too, Mom,

04:25.733 --> 04:26.825
just like the rest of us.

04:26.901 --> 04:29.461
But not in this town.

04:31.038 --> 04:33.438
My mother never
wanted to stay in Bay City.

04:33.507 --> 04:35.941
I think she married my stepfather Ted

04:36.010 --> 04:40.003
because he was so nice
and so clean.

04:40.081 --> 04:42.413
Being an ice skating instructor
made him seem cleaner.

04:42.483 --> 04:46.317
She missed my real father,
who was Egyptian,

04:46.387 --> 04:48.252
dark, and romantic.

04:53.294 --> 04:57.230
One Christmas Eve
I heard my parents arguing.

05:01.802 --> 05:05.135
I didn't know anything
until he was gone.

05:08.376 --> 05:11.607
He drove away in our brown Valiant.

05:15.516 --> 05:17.177
I'm sorry.

05:17.251 --> 05:19.242
Oh, I'm sorry.

05:19.320 --> 05:20.810
I'm so sorry.

05:33.467 --> 05:35.458
You're awfully quiet.

05:37.505 --> 05:39.598
You said we'd see
an Indian reservation.

05:39.674 --> 05:41.403
When we get to one,
we will see one.

05:41.475 --> 05:43.500
Sweetie, don't mumble.

05:43.577 --> 05:46.011
How are you gonna be an actress
if you can't speak clearly?

05:46.080 --> 05:48.674
I don't want to be an actress.

05:48.749 --> 05:51.309
I bet we won't even stop
in Las Vegas, will we?

05:51.385 --> 05:53.444
Ah, now, that's what's bothering you.

05:53.521 --> 05:54.783
You said you had a number on him.

05:54.855 --> 05:58.154
I said we would look him up, ok?

05:58.225 --> 05:59.453
When you were 4 years old,

05:59.527 --> 06:02.257
your father left you just
in the middle of the night.

06:02.330 --> 06:04.093
So, what?
You left my stepfather

06:04.165 --> 06:06.725
in the middle of the afternoon.

06:06.801 --> 06:07.733
I miss Ted.

06:07.802 --> 06:09.030
Nobody misses Ted.
He's boring.

06:09.103 --> 06:10.195
Then why'd you marry him?

06:10.271 --> 06:13.866
That's none of your business.

06:13.941 --> 06:16.501
Besides, he was running
around with other women.

06:16.577 --> 06:18.704
That's not true.
You made that up.

06:18.779 --> 06:20.644
You wanted him to,
so you could catch him

06:20.715 --> 06:22.273
and take him to court
and get all his money.

06:22.350 --> 06:24.875
You little snoop.

06:24.952 --> 06:26.249
And Ted is not a homosexual.

06:26.320 --> 06:27.617
I never said that.

06:27.688 --> 06:28.620
Yes, you did.

06:28.689 --> 06:29.553
Oh, no, I did not.

06:29.623 --> 06:30.612
Oh, yes, you did.

06:30.691 --> 06:31.749
Maybe I inferred it,
but I never said it.

06:31.826 --> 06:32.815
"Light in the loafers"

06:32.893 --> 06:35.327
is not exactly the same thing.

06:35.396 --> 06:36.863
All right, Mother.

06:36.931 --> 06:39.297
Ted said he loves you,

06:39.367 --> 06:41.232
and that he was worried that
you were seeing other people,

06:41.302 --> 06:42.860
which you probably were.

06:42.937 --> 06:45.132
All right, that is it.
I have had it with you.

06:45.206 --> 06:47.106
If you miss Ted so much,
you go find Ted.

06:47.174 --> 06:49.904
Go on, get out ofthe car.
Out! O-u-t, out!

06:49.977 --> 06:51.410
You said we'd see
buffalo in Nebraska.

06:51.479 --> 06:52.946
There were no buffalo.

06:53.013 --> 06:54.002
Tough shit!
Get out of the car!

08:17.264 --> 08:20.028
Ted is going to be
an ice skating instructor

08:20.100 --> 08:21.260
for the rest of his life.

08:21.335 --> 08:23.769
Your cousin Benny is going
to be a garage mechanic.

08:23.838 --> 08:25.533
Lolly is never
going to leave the bank.

08:25.606 --> 08:27.836
Your cousin Hal's
already drinking liquor.

08:27.908 --> 08:29.876
And Sylvia and the baby
can barely breathe.

08:29.944 --> 08:31.309
They're gonna suffocate back there,

08:31.378 --> 08:33.778
but I now have a job teaching

08:33.847 --> 08:35.941
in the Los Angeles school system.

08:36.015 --> 08:37.916
I have an M.A. in early education

08:37.985 --> 08:39.316
which I have just thrown away

08:39.385 --> 08:41.013
in that dink junior high school
back there,

08:41.087 --> 08:42.749
so you forget about the buffalo

08:42.823 --> 08:44.518
and the goddamn Indians.

08:44.592 --> 08:47.755
You are a beautiful girl
with great potential.

08:47.828 --> 08:49.693
I'm not gonna see your future
as some nothing girl

08:49.763 --> 08:51.492
in a nothing factory
in a nothing town.

08:51.565 --> 08:54.159
You are 14 years old,

08:54.235 --> 08:56.169
you've always had enough to eat,

08:56.237 --> 08:57.864
you've always had
a roof over your head,

08:57.938 --> 08:59.599
and if you stick with me,
you always will,

08:59.673 --> 09:01.538
because I am your mother,

09:01.609 --> 09:03.440
and I know what is best for you

09:03.511 --> 09:05.672
because that is my job.

09:05.746 --> 09:08.738
Plus you're gonna go
to school in Beverly Hills,

09:08.816 --> 09:09.942
which is only
the best school district

09:10.017 --> 09:11.484
in the United States.

09:11.552 --> 09:13.019
And you'll be a child actor

09:13.087 --> 09:14.179
while you're still a child.

09:16.390 --> 09:19.917
You don't have a job
in the Los Angeles school district.

09:19.994 --> 09:21.325
I will have.

09:21.395 --> 09:23.590
I have an interview
and a great outfit.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.188
Are you hungry?

09:25.266 --> 09:27.234
Excuse me.

09:27.301 --> 09:29.269
I don't know.

09:29.336 --> 09:31.531
Great. So am I.

09:31.605 --> 09:33.766
So...

09:33.841 --> 09:36.071
Will you look at that car?

09:36.143 --> 09:38.771
Is that the most
beautiful automobile

09:38.846 --> 09:40.211
you've ever seen?

09:40.281 --> 09:44.183
No. I hate that car.
I miss the Plymouth.

09:45.419 --> 09:49.446
Baby, nobody misses the Plymouth.

09:51.225 --> 09:52.453
It's your color.

09:52.526 --> 09:54.994
Yeah, it is, isn't it?

09:55.062 --> 09:57.428
Oh, look at this.

09:57.498 --> 10:00.058
It's so beautiful.

10:00.134 --> 10:01.999
How does it feel?

10:02.069 --> 10:03.934
Sublime.

10:04.004 --> 10:05.835
Mom, we can't afford this car.

10:05.906 --> 10:07.203
We have some money in savings,

10:07.274 --> 10:10.766
and I can dip into
the teachers' retirement fund.

10:11.078 --> 10:13.308
This car does not belong in Bay City,

10:13.380 --> 10:14.938
and neither do we.

10:16.083 --> 10:20.611
We're going to drive
to Beverly Hills

10:20.688 --> 10:22.451
in this car.

11:07.201 --> 11:10.364
Mom, this place
looks expensive.

11:10.437 --> 11:12.166
I'll worry about that, ok?

11:12.239 --> 11:13.866
Now that we're in Beverly Hills,

11:13.941 --> 11:16.739
maybe you should change
your name to Heather.

11:20.114 --> 11:22.241
Mmm, it smells so nice here.

11:22.316 --> 11:23.248
How much is the room?

11:23.317 --> 11:24.511
It's 1,200.

11:24.585 --> 11:25.643
A night?

11:25.719 --> 11:26.811
Yes.

11:26.887 --> 11:29.447
I don't know
that it's large enough.

11:29.523 --> 11:31.150
Do you have any villas?

11:31.225 --> 11:33.693
There are no villas
available right now.

11:33.761 --> 11:35.160
Mom, I'm tired.

11:35.229 --> 11:37.493
Where are we gonna sleep tonight?

11:46.040 --> 11:47.473
Sweet pea,

11:47.541 --> 11:51.534
you are just as pretty
as these girls on TV.

11:51.612 --> 11:54.012
In fact, I think you're prettier.

11:57.584 --> 12:00.917
Sweetie, are you all right?

12:00.988 --> 12:04.788
'Cause you've been in there
for over an hour.

12:06.794 --> 12:08.421
Ok, well...

12:08.495 --> 12:10.156
I'm gonna go to sleep now.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.993
And I think mayb eyou should soon,

12:12.066 --> 12:15.433
because you need
your beauty rest, ok?

12:15.502 --> 12:17.561
Ok. Good night.

12:23.744 --> 12:27.475
I miss everyone
in Bay City so much.

12:27.548 --> 12:29.641
I don't know how
I'm going to survive

12:29.717 --> 12:31.582
without my cousin Benny.

12:33.454 --> 12:35.445
And my best friend,

12:35.522 --> 12:36.989
good little Mary.

12:37.057 --> 12:41.255
Serious Mary, Benny, and I.

12:41.328 --> 12:43.626
We were inseparable.

12:43.697 --> 12:45.062
Benny!

12:45.132 --> 12:46.429
I made this for you.

12:46.500 --> 12:48.229
Say good-bye to your cousin!

12:48.302 --> 12:53.934
It's tin and painted on one side
with gold dust.

12:54.007 --> 12:55.235
Not real gold dust.

12:55.309 --> 12:56.767
Ann!

12:56.901 --> 12:58.493
We're ready to go!

13:01.438 --> 13:04.271
Where do you want
the cookies and the sandwiches?

13:04.341 --> 13:06.241
Oh, Mom, thanks.
I'll take them.

13:06.310 --> 13:09.871
You didn't give her all the cookies,
did you, Lillian?

13:09.947 --> 13:12.177
Don't forget to call us
from the road.

13:12.249 --> 13:13.443
You're gonna come visit.

13:13.517 --> 13:15.576
I'm gonna find an apartment
that's got 3 bedrooms.

13:15.653 --> 13:17.211
She doesn't even have
a place to live.

13:17.288 --> 13:18.915
Stop worrying about it, Mom.

13:18.989 --> 13:20.786
If you knew for sure
there was a job out there...

13:20.858 --> 13:21.790
She's got the school job.

13:21.859 --> 13:23.759
Oh, she has no such thing.

13:23.828 --> 13:25.659
She talked to somebody
on the telephone.

13:25.729 --> 13:28.254
When are you gonna start
having some faith in me?

13:28.332 --> 13:29.731
When you begin
to see things as they are.

13:29.800 --> 13:31.893
Don't take any wooden nickels, Adele.

13:31.969 --> 13:33.903
Right, Jimmy.

13:33.971 --> 13:35.836
Ok, thanks.

13:38.008 --> 13:39.839
Sorry, Ted.

13:42.012 --> 13:42.979
I'll write.

13:45.015 --> 13:50.214
Ann, come on!
I'm gonna leave without you!

13:50.287 --> 13:51.618
Benny!

13:52.690 --> 13:53.884
Ben!

14:02.766 --> 14:04.631
I hope you destroyed those pictures

14:04.702 --> 14:06.169
you took of me in my underwear.

14:06.237 --> 14:08.865
I did, Mary, I promise.

14:08.939 --> 14:09.906
OK.

14:11.175 --> 14:14.201
Let's go.
We'll call from the road.

14:14.278 --> 14:15.711
I'll miss you, too, Grandma.

14:15.779 --> 14:18.043
Take care of yourself.

14:18.115 --> 14:20.982
Ann, here.
Just in case you find

14:21.051 --> 14:23.383
a skating rink out there.

14:23.454 --> 14:25.388
Thanks, Ted.

14:25.456 --> 14:29.688
I love you. You're the best stepdad
a girl could have.

14:29.760 --> 14:34.595
You'll always be with me

14:34.665 --> 14:37.395
Always be with me

14:37.468 --> 14:40.096
Part of my heart

14:40.170 --> 14:45.164
Once I'm where I'm going

14:45.242 --> 14:48.734
Look away

14:50.414 --> 14:58.219
Even if it's just in my mind

15:01.258 --> 15:02.384
Oh, here's a good one.

15:02.459 --> 15:07.021
"Pool, walk-in closets, security,

15:07.097 --> 15:08.394
vaulted ceilings."

15:08.465 --> 15:11.525
Vaulted. I love it.

15:11.602 --> 15:12.933
Excuse me.

15:13.003 --> 15:16.200
I'm sorry.
I couldn't help but overhearing.

15:16.273 --> 15:18.707
I thought I might help you.

15:18.776 --> 15:20.767
I'm Gail Letterfine.

15:20.844 --> 15:23.335
Westside Realty.

15:23.414 --> 15:25.109
Oh.

15:25.182 --> 15:27.047
So, what are you looking for?

15:27.117 --> 15:29.483
Something in Beverly Hills.

15:29.553 --> 15:31.953
I'm Adele August.
This is my daughter Ann.

15:32.022 --> 15:34.684
Hi.

15:34.758 --> 15:37.886
She's not awake.
We just moved here from Wisconsin.

15:37.962 --> 15:39.520
Wisconsin?

15:39.596 --> 15:41.120
I don't know anyone
from Wisconsin.

15:41.198 --> 15:43.257
I'm awake.

15:43.334 --> 15:45.029
You live in Beverly Hills?

15:45.102 --> 15:48.469
No. I live in Santa Monica.
Formerly from Bel Air.

15:48.539 --> 15:49.733
Formerly Brentwood.

15:49.807 --> 15:52.275
I've had a lot of formerlys
in my life.

15:54.745 --> 15:57.475
I'm fine now.
I'm single, I'm free,

15:57.548 --> 15:58.981
and I love it.

16:00.050 --> 16:02.280
Most of the time. Yeah.

16:02.353 --> 16:03.786
Excuse me.

16:06.991 --> 16:08.788
She wants to be an actress.

16:08.859 --> 16:11.350
Don't they all?

16:16.567 --> 16:17.898
Operator.

16:17.968 --> 16:20.129
Just tell her it's a collect call
from her granddaughter Ann.

16:20.204 --> 16:21.193
Just one moment.

16:21.271 --> 16:22.329
Tell her I'll pay her back.

16:22.406 --> 16:26.069
Look what we have
along Beverly Vista.

16:26.143 --> 16:28.941
Beverly Hills adjacent.

16:29.013 --> 16:32.039
That's not the posh part
of Beverly Hills,

16:32.116 --> 16:34.346
but it is still within
the school district.

16:39.456 --> 16:41.686
Sweet pea, what you doing?
Are you OK?

16:41.759 --> 16:42.783
Mm-hmm.

16:42.860 --> 16:45.795
Gail found something for us.
What a woman.

16:45.863 --> 16:48.263
She is raising 3 teenagers by herself.

16:48.332 --> 16:49.799
Husband ran off
with an accountant,

16:49.867 --> 16:51.027
and she can't get
a dime out of him.

16:51.101 --> 16:54.093
Come with me while I pee.
Come on. Also...

16:54.171 --> 16:56.401
she didn't say so, but...

16:56.473 --> 16:58.270
I think she has a glass eye.

16:58.342 --> 16:59.366
You know...

16:59.443 --> 17:01.343
it makes somebody interesting.

17:01.412 --> 17:03.676
You know what I mean?
Interesting in a mysterious way.

17:03.747 --> 17:06.307
Interesting in a kind of a...

17:15.592 --> 17:17.787
Hey, you want a ride?

17:20.196 --> 17:23.325
Ann, there you are.
Your mom's looking for you.

17:23.400 --> 17:24.833
I saw her.

17:24.902 --> 17:28.804
You know, I think that
we might have found a place.

17:30.340 --> 17:33.036
Honey, I know that it's hard
at first, making changes,

17:33.110 --> 17:35.408
but you have to get used to it.

17:35.479 --> 17:37.743
Life is full of them.

17:37.815 --> 17:39.077
Ann, where did you go?

17:39.149 --> 17:40.946
I was in there talking
and talking to you.

17:41.018 --> 17:43.714
I come out here and you're gone.

17:54.031 --> 17:56.226
Your love

17:56.300 --> 17:58.894
Is better than ice cream

17:58.969 --> 18:04.430
Better than anything else
that I've tried

18:04.508 --> 18:06.703
Your love

18:06.777 --> 18:09.473
Is better than ice cream

18:09.546 --> 18:15.781
But everyone here knows how to cry

18:17.588 --> 18:21.388
It's a long way down

18:22.759 --> 18:31.429
It's a long way down

18:31.502 --> 18:35.598
To the place where we started from

18:37.374 --> 18:39.274
You didn't get the job.

18:41.478 --> 18:44.606
It's in the bag, baby.

18:44.681 --> 18:47.206
Come here, you.

18:47.284 --> 18:48.216
Serious?

18:48.285 --> 18:49.343
Yes!

18:50.821 --> 18:52.379
I hate my hair.

18:52.456 --> 18:53.980
It's one of your strongest assets.

18:54.057 --> 18:55.217
I'm gonna cut it off.

18:55.292 --> 18:56.520
Over my dead body.

18:56.593 --> 18:57.617
OK.

19:00.697 --> 19:01.629
OK. Let's go.

19:05.102 --> 19:06.660
Can you believe that?

19:12.109 --> 19:13.804
They look like
they're going to the beach.

19:13.877 --> 19:16.209
The intelligent girls are inside.

19:18.715 --> 19:19.943
Bab-

19:21.818 --> 19:23.683
I hate you.

19:23.754 --> 19:27.212
We'll talk about that later, sweetie.
Good luck.

19:27.291 --> 19:29.725
How about good luck for me?

19:29.793 --> 19:31.954
How do I I-look?

19:54.785 --> 19:56.184
Why don't you just back off?

19:56.253 --> 19:57.948
Punk!

19:58.021 --> 20:00.046
Come on, let's go!

20:00.123 --> 20:01.249
Everybody,

20:01.325 --> 20:04.556
this is our new speech pathologist,
Adele August.

20:04.628 --> 20:06.858
Adele is from Bay City, Wisconsin.

20:06.930 --> 20:09.160
America's dairyland.

20:09.233 --> 20:10.165
Ah, Wisconsin.

20:10.234 --> 20:11.166
Yes.

20:11.235 --> 20:12.327
George Franklin, history.

20:12.402 --> 20:13.369
George. History.

20:14.938 --> 20:16.929
Room 12 is to the right, right?

20:17.007 --> 20:17.996
Let me show you.

20:18.075 --> 20:19.007
Follow me.

20:19.076 --> 20:20.543
Thank you so much.

20:24.915 --> 20:26.576
Not exactly Bay City,

20:26.650 --> 20:28.242
but you get used to it.

20:32.356 --> 20:36.486
Mmm. Is that-
Did they throw out that furniture?

20:36.560 --> 20:38.221
Is that garbage?

20:38.295 --> 20:39.284
Mm-hmm.

20:39.363 --> 20:40.330
Unbelievable.

20:43.367 --> 20:46.131
Honey, don't scratch the car.

20:46.203 --> 20:49.070
On our days off
we would drive to relax.

20:49.139 --> 20:51.835
We drove just anywhere.

20:53.343 --> 20:55.208
My mother was in awe of the homes

20:55.279 --> 20:56.405
and the palm trees

20:56.480 --> 21:00.211
and real movie stars
on public sidewalks.

21:00.284 --> 21:02.252
She was in love.

21:02.319 --> 21:03.809
In love with Beverly Hills.

21:03.887 --> 21:05.013
Oh, I like that one.

21:05.088 --> 21:07.181
Over there, with the circular driveway.

21:07.257 --> 21:09.987
I want the room in the corner.
I can climb out that window.

21:10.060 --> 21:11.527
I'll take the one in the back,

21:11.595 --> 21:13.586
overlooking the pool.

21:17.367 --> 21:19.767
Mmm. That one's a beauty,

21:19.936 --> 21:23.372
with the cute blue shutters.

21:23.440 --> 21:25.908
Oh, look at this house.

21:25.976 --> 21:28.638
This is the house I want.

21:28.712 --> 21:30.373
That is beautiful. Come on.

21:30.447 --> 21:31.846
Mom, it's by appointment only.

21:31.915 --> 21:32.904
It's all right.

21:32.983 --> 21:34.780
It says,
"Do not disturb occupants."

21:34.851 --> 21:38.446
Just smile.
We'll be fine. It's ok.

21:38.522 --> 21:40.615
I appreciate it.
Please think about it.

21:40.691 --> 21:42.090
You're the realtor.

21:42.159 --> 21:43.683
Hi. How can I help you?

21:43.760 --> 21:46.320
Look at this sweet-
Oh, he gave me a kiss.

21:46.396 --> 21:47.363
This is Callie.

21:47.431 --> 21:49.228
Hi, Callie.
And you must be the owner.

21:49.299 --> 21:50.266
My baby. Yes, I am.

21:50.334 --> 21:51.801
Well, I'm Adele August. Hello.

21:51.868 --> 21:53.563
And this is my baby, Heather.

21:53.637 --> 21:54.695
Hi.

21:54.771 --> 21:56.329
Excuse me.
Can I help you?

21:56.406 --> 21:58.306
I know we should
have an appointment,

21:58.375 --> 22:01.503
but my husband will be
practicing medicine at UCLA.

22:01.578 --> 22:02.772
That's just a few minutes
from here.

22:02.846 --> 22:04.780
Exactly, so we were driving by,

22:04.848 --> 22:05.837
and we just had to stop.

22:05.916 --> 22:08.749
I would be so grateful

22:08.819 --> 22:10.616
if you would let us
see the house.

22:10.687 --> 22:11.619
Do you mind?

22:11.688 --> 22:12.712
Not at all.
Please, come in.

22:12.789 --> 22:13.721
Here's my card.

22:13.790 --> 22:15.417
Here's a setup on the property.

22:15.492 --> 22:17.357
Thank you.

22:17.427 --> 22:19.691
The house was built originally
in the 1920s,

22:19.763 --> 22:22.425
so it maintains
all its original integrity.

22:22.499 --> 22:24.399
You also have
a wood-burning fire place here.

22:24.468 --> 22:27.335
There are 7 in the entire house.

22:27.404 --> 22:30.134
There is so much light.
Look at this light.

22:30.207 --> 22:32.573
It's a very happy, happy house.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.803
- So happy, isn't it, Heather?
- Happy.

22:34.878 --> 22:37.438
And here we have
a beautiful bright bedroom.

22:37.514 --> 22:39.414
And you can see the pool from here.

22:39.483 --> 22:42.213
Oh, it's a lovely master suite,
isn't it?

22:42.285 --> 22:44.810
No. This is my daughter's bedroom.

22:44.888 --> 22:46.617
She's away at college now.

22:46.690 --> 22:47.782
Oh. Where is she going?

22:47.858 --> 22:49.826
Back East. Princeton, actually.

22:49.893 --> 22:53.420
I want to go to college back East.

22:53.497 --> 22:54.987
You must miss her terribly.

22:55.065 --> 22:56.999
But we're so very proud.

22:57.067 --> 23:00.264
Well, Daddy will
be here next week.

23:00.337 --> 23:02.737
I really want him
to see this house.

23:02.806 --> 23:05.434
Let me show you
the master bedroom right now.

23:05.509 --> 23:08.910
It's got a great
his-and-her walk-in closet.

23:08.979 --> 23:12.005
It also has a fantastic
Jacuzzi tub.

23:12.082 --> 23:14.175
I love a Jacuzzi.

23:38.875 --> 23:39.842
Hello.

23:39.910 --> 23:41.343
What's up, pervert?

23:41.411 --> 23:42.378
Who is this?

23:42.446 --> 23:43.743
It's hot stuff.

23:43.814 --> 23:46.476
Ann.

23:46.550 --> 23:48.177
Hey, Benny.

23:48.251 --> 23:49.548
Where are you?

23:49.619 --> 23:53.055
Making a highly illegal phone call
in somebody's bedroom.

23:53.123 --> 23:54.522
What are you doing right now?

23:54.591 --> 23:56.354
Hauser's taking us to the park.

23:56.426 --> 23:58.724
He got that new truck.

23:58.795 --> 23:59.762
Why are you whispering?

23:59.830 --> 24:00.922
Where are you?

24:00.997 --> 24:02.760
How's Grandma?

24:02.833 --> 24:06.269
Fine. What did you mean
you're in someone's bedroom?

24:06.336 --> 24:07.598
I'll tell you
when I write you another letter.

24:07.671 --> 24:08.660
You get my last one?

24:08.738 --> 24:11.434
Yeah, yeah, I got 'em all.

24:11.508 --> 24:13.874
I like the one
where she kicked you out of the car.

24:13.944 --> 24:14.876
She really did that?

24:14.945 --> 24:17.209
She's crazy.
She still is.

24:17.280 --> 24:19.748
I think I might kill her
in her sleep.

24:19.816 --> 24:20.976
Heather.

24:21.051 --> 24:22.018
I have to go.

24:22.085 --> 24:23.211
Heather Ann.

24:24.538 --> 24:26.563
Oh, that was so much fun,
wasn't it?

24:26.640 --> 24:28.403
Why'd you tell that lady
that we'd buy the house?

24:28.475 --> 24:29.533
I said we might buy the house.

24:29.609 --> 24:31.042
That my father's coming,
that he's a doctor.

24:31.111 --> 24:32.043
Cardiologist.

24:32.112 --> 24:33.079
I couldn't believe you.

24:33.146 --> 24:34.340
What were you doing

24:34.414 --> 24:36.939
up in the daughter's room
all that time?

24:37.017 --> 24:38.348
Calling Benny.

24:39.853 --> 24:41.286
What?

24:41.354 --> 24:42.981
Ann!

24:43.056 --> 24:45.490
I had to tell her that your father

24:45.559 --> 24:47.390
the doctor was coming
because a woman like that

24:47.461 --> 24:49.793
who gets all ofher money from
her husband, she's not gonna believe

24:49.863 --> 24:51.524
a woman like me can afford
a house like that.

24:51.598 --> 24:53.361
A woman like you
can't afford a house like that.

24:53.433 --> 24:55.594
You can't even afford
the bathroom to that house.

24:55.669 --> 24:58.194
Be optimistic

24:58.271 --> 24:59.397
Don't you be a grumpy

24:59.473 --> 25:01.407
When the road gets bumpy

25:01.475 --> 25:02.737
Just smile, smile, smile

25:02.809 --> 25:03.798
And be happy

25:07.347 --> 25:08.644
Morning, Adele.

25:08.715 --> 25:11.081
Morning, George.

25:11.151 --> 25:13.449
Grand Coolie Dam.
Ever been there, Adele?

25:13.520 --> 25:15.010
Nope.

25:15.088 --> 25:16.453
Hoover Dam?

25:16.523 --> 25:18.753
No.

25:18.825 --> 25:21.157
I'm not really into dams.

25:22.562 --> 25:23.859
I am gonna get a lawyer

25:23.930 --> 25:25.693
and sue her
for invasion of privacy,

25:25.765 --> 25:28.666
so get your nose
out of my diary, Mother.

25:28.735 --> 25:30.726
That's so cool.
I'd never think of that.

25:30.804 --> 25:31.964
Did she say anything?

25:32.038 --> 25:34.302
She played dumb,
but she never did it again.

25:34.374 --> 25:36.001
I wish my parents
would just leave me alone.

25:36.076 --> 25:37.202
I love being alone.

25:37.277 --> 25:39.177
I can't wait for
the house to be empty.

25:39.246 --> 25:40.679
Hi.

25:40.747 --> 25:42.942
Hey, Peter.

25:43.016 --> 25:45.484
You run good.
Got good form.

25:45.552 --> 25:47.520
Yeah.

25:47.587 --> 25:50.852
There's not a cloud
in the sky today, huh?

25:52.225 --> 25:54.125
Hey, you ever read T.S. Eliot?

25:54.194 --> 25:55.786
What?

25:55.862 --> 25:57.853
Four Quartets,
it's really good.

25:59.633 --> 26:02.431
Why do you run with a book?

26:02.502 --> 26:04.436
I don't know.
Balance, I guess.

26:07.774 --> 26:10.038
Here's the Kariba Dam.

26:10.110 --> 26:11.634
It impounds the Zambezi River,

26:11.711 --> 26:13.906
forms Kariba Lake.

26:13.980 --> 26:15.072
- It's nice.
- Hmm.

26:15.148 --> 26:16.513
I went there.

26:16.583 --> 26:20.144
After college.
I painted a picture of it.

26:20.220 --> 26:21.812
You painted pictures of dams?

26:21.888 --> 26:23.185
Mm-hmm.

26:23.256 --> 26:24.723
That was my dream-
To travel the world

26:24.791 --> 26:26.418
and paint pictures.

26:26.493 --> 26:28.688
Hmm. What happened?

26:28.762 --> 26:31.424
Hmm. I don't know.

26:31.498 --> 26:33.523
One damn thing
led to another damn thing.

26:33.600 --> 26:35.397
Ha ha!

26:35.468 --> 26:37.459
I don't know.

26:37.537 --> 26:39.562
I don't know.
I became a history teacher.

26:41.107 --> 26:43.405
But one of these days, I'll...

26:43.476 --> 26:44.408
One of these days-

26:44.477 --> 26:46.445
Oh, my God.
Get away from my car!

26:47.714 --> 26:48.646
Oh, my God, look what he's doing!

26:48.715 --> 26:49.977
Hey.
Hey, hey, hey!

26:50.050 --> 26:51.711
No! Stop it!

26:51.785 --> 26:54.253
Oh, my God.
Look how deep this scratch-

26:54.321 --> 26:55.720
Look what he did to my car.

26:55.789 --> 26:58.622
Mom, it's just a scratch.

26:58.692 --> 27:01.024
Just a scratch?

27:01.094 --> 27:02.391
Do you know how much
it's going to cost

27:02.462 --> 27:04.953
to fix "just a scratch"?

27:05.031 --> 27:06.362
Oh, I can't work
at this school anymore.

27:06.433 --> 27:08.230
I can't talk to you anymore, either!

27:08.301 --> 27:09.233
No sympathy.

27:11.438 --> 27:14.373
The tiles are all cracked...

27:14.441 --> 27:15.874
and chipped.

27:15.942 --> 27:16.966
I'm sinking here,

27:17.043 --> 27:19.068
and I'm the one
that has to keep us afloat.

27:19.145 --> 27:21.739
Every time I think
I'm trying so hard,

27:21.815 --> 27:22.873
it's getting better,

27:22.949 --> 27:24.439
and we're starting to get somewhere,

27:24.517 --> 27:27.111
just, everything falls apart.

27:27.187 --> 27:29.052
Aah! Jesus!

27:29.122 --> 27:32.182
Nothing works in this apartment!

27:32.258 --> 27:33.520
- Mom?
- Aah!

27:33.593 --> 27:37.029
It's just a scratch on the car.

27:41.501 --> 27:43.162
Maybe if you got yourself

27:43.236 --> 27:45.966
a little after-school job,

27:46.039 --> 27:48.633
you'd know what
I'm talking about.

27:48.708 --> 27:50.869
People your age have no idea

27:50.944 --> 27:53.003
how much things cost,
how to manage money.

27:53.079 --> 27:55.013
What is that now?

27:55.081 --> 27:57.481
You didn't pay the bill again,
did you?

27:57.550 --> 28:01.953
I did pay the bill!
I did pay it!

28:04.724 --> 28:06.419
Well, maybe I won't even
pay the bill again.

28:06.493 --> 28:08.222
Maybe we'll just...

28:08.294 --> 28:11.127
Ha!
We could live...

28:11.197 --> 28:12.596
in the dark

28:12.666 --> 28:14.531
like little...

28:14.601 --> 28:17.001
bears in a cave,
huh, Pooh Bear?

28:17.070 --> 28:18.833
Hmm?

28:18.905 --> 28:19.837
Just...

28:25.779 --> 28:28.213
Ok, let's go to Denny's.

28:31.551 --> 28:33.542
Ann?

28:33.620 --> 28:35.781
Ann, where are you?

28:35.855 --> 28:37.789
I'm going to bed.

28:47.467 --> 28:50.903
I really thought I paid that bill.

29:01.581 --> 29:05.017
I really think I did pay it.

29:21.701 --> 29:24.329
So, I love you and
say hi to Benny for me

29:24.404 --> 29:26.634
and Uncle Jimmy
and Aunt Carol and...

29:26.706 --> 29:27.730
OK, I love you.
Lots of kisses.

29:27.807 --> 29:29.035
Bye.

29:29.109 --> 29:30.337
Hi, Mom.

29:30.410 --> 29:32.605
How are y'all doing?

29:32.679 --> 29:34.408
What isn't fair?

29:34.481 --> 29:36.039
Well, I put her on
because what's fair

29:36.116 --> 29:38.084
is for your granddaughter
to have a decent home

29:38.151 --> 29:39.675
to live in,
and we can't do that

29:39.753 --> 29:42.244
unless we have some cash
for a down payment.

29:42.322 --> 29:43.653
What I need from you

29:43.723 --> 29:45.315
is some help.

29:45.391 --> 29:46.483
Well...

29:46.559 --> 29:49.027
sell my land, that's how.

29:49.095 --> 29:51.529
It's the land that Daddy-

29:54.834 --> 29:55.892
She hung up.

29:55.969 --> 29:58.437
Grandma hung up on you?

30:03.143 --> 30:04.075
Yeah.

30:14.120 --> 30:16.418
Let's get dressed up
and go out to dinner.

30:16.489 --> 30:18.047
What?

30:19.159 --> 30:20.456
You love that
little French restaurant.

30:20.527 --> 30:22.859
That's -
That's just what we need.

30:24.464 --> 30:26.056
We need a bed for me.
We need a desk.

30:26.132 --> 30:28.362
We need sheets.
We need towels.

30:28.434 --> 30:30.493
We don't need to go out to eat
to a French restaurant.

30:30.570 --> 30:32.037
Oh, honey.

30:32.105 --> 30:34.335
My daddy always used to say,

30:34.407 --> 30:35.840
"When life gets rough

30:35.909 --> 30:37.740
and you only have a dime
in your pocket,

30:37.811 --> 30:40.644
go get your shoes shined."

30:42.615 --> 30:44.139
Get dressed.

30:46.986 --> 30:48.044
Hmm.

30:50.123 --> 30:51.784
Seems they raised their prices.

30:51.858 --> 30:53.723
I'll tell you what.

30:53.793 --> 30:54.725
Why don't the two of us -

30:54.794 --> 30:56.921
Good afternoon.
Would you like to hear our specials?

30:56.996 --> 30:58.987
I don't think so.
We know what we want.

30:59.065 --> 31:00.157
I'd like to hear the specials.

31:00.233 --> 31:01.165
Thank you.

31:01.234 --> 31:02.792
Ok. We have the veal St. Jacques

31:02.869 --> 31:03.858
and a lovely coq au vin-

31:03.937 --> 31:06.269
I think we'll have
2 small garden salads

31:06.339 --> 31:07.271
and share the veal St. Jacques.

31:07.340 --> 31:08.364
Don't you think, honey?

31:08.441 --> 31:09.965
You know what?
I don't really want to share.

31:10.043 --> 31:11.510
I'm kind of hungry, so...

31:11.578 --> 31:12.909
Why don't you have
the veal St. Jacques,

31:12.979 --> 31:16.278
and I'll have
the duck I'orange, please.

31:16.349 --> 31:17.281
And would you like an appetizer?

31:17.350 --> 31:18.282
- I don't think so.
- Yes.

31:18.351 --> 31:20.546
I'll have the shrimp

31:20.620 --> 31:21.985
in the garlic sauce.

31:22.055 --> 31:23.317
And anything to drink?

31:23.389 --> 31:24.754
Just water.

31:24.824 --> 31:26.382
Bottled. A big bottle,

31:26.459 --> 31:27.517
please. Thanks.

31:28.928 --> 31:30.361
OK.
Thank you.

31:36.336 --> 31:38.065
You know what?
I'm really hungry,

31:38.137 --> 31:40.401
and it's not like
we're at Denny's,

31:40.473 --> 31:42.100
so if someone comes in

31:42.175 --> 31:44.040
and sees me eating duck I'orange,

31:44.110 --> 31:46.943
who knows what effect
it'll have on my life.

31:48.915 --> 31:50.849
Sit up straight.

31:50.917 --> 31:52.384
You're slouching.

31:55.388 --> 31:58.380
I took out an ad
in the newspaper once-

31:58.458 --> 32:00.016
"15-year-old seeks home-

32:01.094 --> 32:04.029
Neat, pretty, good student."

32:04.097 --> 32:05.359
I got 79 replies.

32:07.300 --> 32:09.825
I never opened them.

32:09.903 --> 32:14.363
I was afraid the temptation
would be too great.

32:18.878 --> 32:20.539
Passion.

32:20.613 --> 32:22.774
It was our first Christmas
away from home.

32:22.849 --> 32:24.373
Do you customize scents?

32:24.450 --> 32:25.781
No? Oh, that's a shame.

32:25.852 --> 32:26.784
You should do that.

32:26.853 --> 32:28.150
My mother paid enough of our bills

32:28.221 --> 32:30.655
so that we could buy
presents for everyone.

32:30.723 --> 32:33.248
That's pretty cute.

32:33.326 --> 32:34.987
Lavender.
What do you think?

32:35.061 --> 32:36.426
Uhh.

32:36.496 --> 32:37.428
- Yeah?
- Mmm.

32:37.497 --> 32:38.828
We didn't buy too much,

32:38.898 --> 32:39.956
considering I love that store.

32:40.033 --> 32:41.523
I don't know what to get Benny.

32:41.601 --> 32:43.068
What did you get me?

32:43.136 --> 32:44.068
Come on, you got me something.

32:44.137 --> 32:45.069
I didn't get you anything.

32:45.138 --> 32:46.162
Oh, yes, you did.

32:46.239 --> 32:47.263
What'd you get me?

32:47.340 --> 32:48.864
I got you lots.
I'm dying to show it to you.

32:48.942 --> 32:50.068
No. Don't show me.

32:50.243 --> 32:51.642
Ann, hi.

32:51.711 --> 32:53.736
Isn't it obscene,
all this money being spent?

32:53.813 --> 32:54.905
- Yeah.
- Hi.

32:54.981 --> 32:56.846
Hi, I'm Janice Pearlman.
I'm in Ann's homeroom.

32:56.916 --> 32:57.848
I'm Ann's mother.

32:57.917 --> 32:59.544
She's my mother.

32:59.619 --> 33:00.551
Hi.

33:00.620 --> 33:02.281
You-You look alike, you two.

33:02.355 --> 33:03.287
- No.
- Oh, thanks.

33:03.356 --> 33:04.687
No, we don't.
I look like my dad.

33:04.757 --> 33:05.689
Just his chin.

33:05.758 --> 33:07.589
I like your chin.
I do.

33:07.660 --> 33:08.820
Anyway, listen, I got to go,

33:08.895 --> 33:10.453
because my mother's
waiting over there,

33:10.530 --> 33:12.760
but Christmas Day,
we're having a party at the house

33:12.832 --> 33:14.060
from 4:00 to 8:00.

33:14.133 --> 33:15.065
Will you come, both of you?

33:15.134 --> 33:16.294
It's our annual thing.

33:16.369 --> 33:17.996
- I-
- Thanks. That's sweet.

33:18.071 --> 33:19.038
Really?
Well, please.

33:19.105 --> 33:21.369
I'll tell you more at school.
Everybody's going to come, though.

33:21.441 --> 33:23.534
- See you later.
- Bye.

33:24.610 --> 33:25.542
Hi.

33:25.611 --> 33:27.272
Everybody likes her.

33:27.347 --> 33:28.439
She's on student council,

33:28.514 --> 33:29.981
and her brother's the editor

33:30.049 --> 33:31.311
of the school newspaper.

33:31.384 --> 33:33.113
What does her father do?

33:33.186 --> 33:34.619
I think he's a doctor.

33:34.687 --> 33:38.054
Huh. Well, it might be fun.

33:38.124 --> 33:39.751
You want to go?

33:39.826 --> 33:41.418
Do you want me to go?

33:41.494 --> 33:42.927
I guess it'll
give us a chance

33:42.996 --> 33:44.725
to kind of show ourselves off,

33:44.797 --> 33:47.357
and the car is looking great again.

33:47.433 --> 33:48.365
Great.

33:51.371 --> 33:53.032
Her mom looked...

33:53.106 --> 33:54.539
very elegant.

33:56.075 --> 33:57.508
You're elegant, Mom.

34:00.246 --> 34:01.543
We both are.

34:01.614 --> 34:03.377
We've got taste, huh?

34:03.449 --> 34:04.711
That's one thing-
People look at us, and they say,

34:04.784 --> 34:08.686
"Look at that great-looking
mother and daughter."

34:09.755 --> 34:10.688
Where do they live?

34:11.991 --> 34:13.322
Mom, why are you doing this?

34:13.393 --> 34:15.121
Which one is it, honey?
Point it out.

34:15.194 --> 34:16.456
That one.

34:16.529 --> 34:17.996
Now let's go home.

34:18.063 --> 34:20.554
Oh, my God.

34:24.370 --> 34:28.033
It goes all the way
around the block.

34:29.208 --> 34:30.902
Yeah.
We're going to a party tonight.

34:30.976 --> 34:32.877
Yeah. Mom and I are both going.

34:32.945 --> 34:34.139
Do you want to talk to her again?

34:34.213 --> 34:36.340
Just say merry Christmas.

34:36.416 --> 34:37.382
Merry Christmas.

34:37.449 --> 34:39.782
Merry Christmas to everybody.

34:39.851 --> 34:43.413
I love you.
Give a big hug to Benny for me.

34:43.489 --> 34:46.617
Ok. Bye-bye.
Love you. Bye.

34:46.692 --> 34:48.056
I'm going to go get dressed

34:48.127 --> 34:51.062
and try on my new necklace.

35:11.751 --> 35:13.651
Mom, it's 4:00.

35:13.719 --> 35:16.586
Are you going to get dressed?

35:16.656 --> 35:19.181
It takes you an hour
to get ready. We're-

35:19.258 --> 35:21.283
The party's going to be over by then.

35:23.029 --> 35:24.257
I thought you said
you wanted to go.

35:24.330 --> 35:25.490
Honey, what I want

35:25.565 --> 35:28.193
is to get all of these pine needles

35:28.267 --> 35:29.632
and vacuum those closets.

35:29.702 --> 35:30.691
They're filled with dust.

35:30.770 --> 35:32.670
And maybe wash the kitchen floor,

35:32.738 --> 35:33.864
because I realized, sweetheart,

35:33.940 --> 35:36.170
that the thing that's going
to make me most happy

35:36.242 --> 35:37.539
is to just look around this place

35:37.610 --> 35:40.408
and see that it is spick-and-span.

35:41.981 --> 35:44.609
But it's the one fun thing
we can do for Christmas.

35:44.684 --> 35:46.675
Well, then, you should go.
You should definitely go.

35:46.752 --> 35:48.583
I mean, all your friends are
going to be there, right?

35:48.654 --> 35:50.519
And that boy Peter-
Is that his name?

35:50.590 --> 35:52.615
He'll be there, right?

35:52.692 --> 35:55.354
What are you going to do?
It's Christmas.

35:55.428 --> 35:56.986
Oh, don't worry about me.

35:57.063 --> 35:58.530
I've just got a million things

35:58.598 --> 35:59.758
that I'm going to do.

35:59.832 --> 36:02.232
I want our first Christmas

36:02.301 --> 36:05.236
in Los Angeles to be perfect.

36:10.710 --> 36:13.110
Aren't things-
Aren't things bad enough here?

36:15.181 --> 36:16.705
I don't know
why you're doing this to me.

36:21.053 --> 36:23.749
You're right.
I'm sorry.

36:23.823 --> 36:25.085
Want me to drive you there?

36:25.158 --> 36:26.318
- Want me to drive you?
- No.

36:26.392 --> 36:27.654
- No.
- Yeah.

36:27.727 --> 36:29.661
No.
I can walk.

36:33.399 --> 36:36.129
All right, well, then, go.

36:38.337 --> 36:39.770
Go ahead.

36:41.307 --> 36:43.673
Otherwise, we're just going
to hang around here all day

36:43.743 --> 36:47.235
talking about our silly
little lives, huh?

36:47.313 --> 36:50.009
Oh, gosh, I just had the...

36:50.082 --> 36:52.983
strongest memory of my father.

36:53.052 --> 36:54.349
I'm going to go.
I'm going to be late.

36:54.420 --> 36:56.684
I'm sorry that you never
really got to know

36:56.756 --> 37:00.248
your grandfather or
your father, for that matter,

37:00.326 --> 37:01.725
and I know it means
something to you

37:01.794 --> 37:03.887
to find your father,

37:03.963 --> 37:05.225
sweetie.

37:06.399 --> 37:08.094
I promise.

37:08.167 --> 37:09.099
We will.

37:09.168 --> 37:10.362
- I'm going.
- Ok.

37:10.436 --> 37:11.630
I'm going.

37:11.704 --> 37:13.467
And maybe we can, um...

37:13.539 --> 37:15.769
We'll talk about your father
when you come back.

37:17.310 --> 37:18.971
I'll be here.
I'm not going anywhere.

37:19.045 --> 37:20.802
I'll wait.

38:06.281 --> 38:08.215
I wish for a place

38:09.484 --> 38:12.578
Where the earth doesn't shake

38:12.654 --> 38:15.088
And if the earth won't be still

38:16.658 --> 38:18.717
Then you and I will

38:27.569 --> 38:31.003
Mmm

38:37.579 --> 38:39.672
I'm sorry.

38:39.748 --> 38:42.683
I thought I could go, but...

38:44.653 --> 38:46.086
I couldn't.

38:55.530 --> 38:58.658
You know what we need?

38:58.733 --> 39:00.701
Some sugar in our blood.

39:00.769 --> 39:04.705
You want to get some ice cream?

39:04.773 --> 39:06.900
I don't want ice cream.

39:06.975 --> 39:08.408
Sure, you do.

39:09.577 --> 39:11.067
Is that what I want, Mom?

39:13.448 --> 39:15.177
It would cheer us up.

39:15.250 --> 39:18.742
Ok, Mother,
let's get our sugar.

39:20.488 --> 39:22.251
And they've got a new flavor.

39:22.324 --> 39:23.552
Great.

39:23.625 --> 39:25.058
Let's go.

39:26.127 --> 39:29.028
I'll get your jacket.

39:30.165 --> 39:31.325
Just one little-

39:31.399 --> 39:33.264
No, no, no, no, no.
We close early today.

39:33.335 --> 39:34.927
Nothing?
It's Christmas.

39:35.003 --> 39:35.992
Ay.

39:36.071 --> 39:37.333
Christmas.

39:37.405 --> 39:38.872
Oh, my God.

39:38.940 --> 39:41.033
Merry Christmas, Officer.

39:41.109 --> 39:42.406
You're not working today, are you?

39:42.477 --> 39:44.069
You see that red curb, ma'am?

39:44.145 --> 39:46.010
See that "No Stopping" sign?

39:46.081 --> 39:48.413
- Oh. Oh.
- Give me your driver's license, please.

39:48.483 --> 39:50.474
I'm so sorry.
I had no idea.

39:50.552 --> 39:51.519
Did you see-

39:51.586 --> 39:53.110
I was just here
to get her an ice cream.

39:53.188 --> 39:55.622
- She needed an ice cream.
- Don't blame it on me.

39:55.690 --> 39:57.555
I'm just explaining
to the officer, sweetheart.

39:57.625 --> 39:59.388
- I hate it when you do this.
- What?

39:59.461 --> 40:00.689
You always do this to me.
You always-

40:00.762 --> 40:03.128
I was explaining to him
it's our Christmas tradition-

40:03.198 --> 40:04.995
I didn't even want ice cream.
She wanted ice cream.

40:05.066 --> 40:06.090
Ann, where are you going?

40:06.167 --> 40:07.099
She'll be back.

40:07.168 --> 40:08.135
Excuse me.
She won't be back.

40:08.203 --> 40:10.103
Hey, hey, hey.
You stay by the car, ok?

40:10.171 --> 40:11.103
Ann?

40:11.172 --> 40:12.537
Lady, wait by the car!

40:12.607 --> 40:13.972
All right.

40:14.042 --> 40:14.974
Ann, come here.

40:15.043 --> 40:15.975
Ann.

40:16.044 --> 40:17.477
Wait.

40:17.545 --> 40:18.603
It was her idea to park there.

40:18.680 --> 40:20.545
I told her not to park there.

40:20.615 --> 40:22.378
I didn't even want any ice cream.

40:22.450 --> 40:23.678
Your mother's trying
to beat a ticket.

40:23.752 --> 40:25.652
Give her one.
She already has a drawer full of them.

40:25.720 --> 40:26.652
Now, now.

40:26.721 --> 40:27.915
Don't talk to me
like a little girl.

40:27.989 --> 40:28.978
I'm not a little girl.

40:31.393 --> 40:33.156
You don't even understand.

40:33.228 --> 40:35.219
I'm going to leave her
one of these days.

40:36.664 --> 40:38.188
I'm sure you will,

40:38.266 --> 40:39.198
but not today.

40:39.267 --> 40:40.529
Why not today?

40:40.602 --> 40:41.569
Well...

40:41.636 --> 40:44.799
you should leave her
when you're calm...

40:44.873 --> 40:46.306
when you're rational.

40:48.643 --> 40:50.907
You leave her
when you're ready not to come back.

40:50.979 --> 40:51.911
You understand?

40:55.316 --> 40:57.477
You from Wisconsin?

40:57.552 --> 40:59.782
How do you know?

40:59.854 --> 41:01.412
Well, your plates.

41:01.489 --> 41:03.889
- You living here now?
- Yes.

41:03.958 --> 41:08.327
- Hey, Ann.
- Lady, I want you to register that car.

41:08.396 --> 41:09.522
Yes, sir.

41:09.597 --> 41:11.497
I want you to get
a California driver's license.

41:11.566 --> 41:14.228
From now on,
start paying attention to the signs.

41:14.302 --> 41:15.428
Yes, sir.

41:15.503 --> 41:17.130
I'm going to be rolling by
in another 2 minutes.

41:17.205 --> 41:19.036
I don't want to see
that vehicle out there.

41:19.107 --> 41:20.574
Yes, sir.

41:20.642 --> 41:21.734
Good.

41:24.579 --> 41:26.171
Merry Christmas, Ann.

41:32.120 --> 41:34.680
Let's move up here.

41:34.756 --> 41:37.156
Did he just wink at you?

41:37.225 --> 41:40.661
That's an unusual
law enforcement officer.

41:40.728 --> 41:42.696
What did he say to you?

41:42.764 --> 41:44.391
He said not to ever
do that to me again.

41:44.466 --> 41:45.398
He said that if you do,

41:45.467 --> 41:46.764
he'll have you taken off to prison

41:46.835 --> 41:47.859
and locked up,

41:47.936 --> 41:49.426
and you'll never, ever see me again,

41:49.504 --> 41:53.565
and you'll have to eat
ice cream on your own.

41:53.641 --> 41:55.268
You went too far
with the ice cream business.

41:55.343 --> 41:56.332
He did not say that.

41:56.411 --> 41:57.742
- Yes, he did.
- No, he did not.

41:57.812 --> 41:59.541
And he wants to adopt me.
He finds me very attractive.

41:59.614 --> 42:01.104
That is not funny.

42:01.182 --> 42:02.877
You do not do this again.

42:02.951 --> 42:03.883
Don't you do this again.

42:03.952 --> 42:04.884
No, don't you do this again.

42:04.953 --> 42:06.648
No, it's you.

42:06.721 --> 42:08.018
Look...

42:08.089 --> 42:10.683
I was just trying to get out
of a parking ticket.

42:10.758 --> 42:11.782
Well, you didn't get one, did you?

42:11.860 --> 42:12.952
Thank you, Ann.
Thank you, Ann,

42:13.027 --> 42:15.461
and your fiancé will be
back here in 2 minutes

42:15.530 --> 42:17.498
to see if we've moved the car.

42:17.565 --> 42:19.430
I will always love that policeman.

42:19.501 --> 42:20.490
That was all me.

42:20.568 --> 42:23.628
He told me what I needed to know.

42:23.705 --> 42:25.263
I will always carry a soft spot

42:25.340 --> 42:27.467
for the Los Angeles Police Department.

42:30.778 --> 42:33.645
I wish he had adopted me.

42:36.784 --> 42:37.751
Grandma told me in a letter

42:37.819 --> 42:39.218
that my father got remarried

42:39.287 --> 42:42.586
and was living in Reno.

42:42.657 --> 42:46.115
How many Hisham Badirs
could there be in Reno?

42:49.797 --> 42:52.027
Hi. Do you have a number for...

42:52.100 --> 42:55.797
for a Mr. Hisham Badir, please?

42:55.870 --> 42:58.737
B-a-d-i-r.

42:58.806 --> 42:59.738
Residence.

42:59.807 --> 43:02.674
H-i-s-h-a-m.

43:06.047 --> 43:07.480
Thank you.

43:14.589 --> 43:16.022
Ok. Thank you.

43:17.091 --> 43:18.023
Bye.

43:27.135 --> 43:28.796
When I was younger,

43:28.870 --> 43:31.100
my mother always hummed
one of my father's tunes

43:31.172 --> 43:33.538
before we went to sleep.

43:33.608 --> 43:36.543
He wrote my mother love songs.

43:40.415 --> 43:42.076
Sometimes, I would imagine my father

43:42.150 --> 43:44.584
showing up to rescue me.

43:48.923 --> 43:50.481
Hi, Ann.

43:50.558 --> 43:52.958
Hello, Peter.

43:53.027 --> 43:55.495
You got that
isosceles triangle thing straight?

43:55.563 --> 43:57.030
Mm-hmm.

43:58.166 --> 43:59.599
That baffles me.

44:02.937 --> 44:04.427
Hey, I got a new trumpet.
You want to see it?

44:06.574 --> 44:08.371
I'm working, Peter.

44:08.443 --> 44:09.910
Right.
Sorry.

44:13.481 --> 44:15.005
Your mom's really pretty.

44:15.083 --> 44:16.550
I'll tell her.

44:19.587 --> 44:20.576
What's your dad do?

44:22.757 --> 44:23.883
He's a songwriter.

44:25.159 --> 44:27.252
Really?
I write some songs.

44:27.328 --> 44:28.590
Yeah. You want to hear one?

44:28.663 --> 44:30.528
Not now, Peter.

44:31.833 --> 44:33.460
You want to feel my pulse?

44:35.103 --> 44:37.037
It's beating really fast.

44:42.844 --> 44:43.776
Ba-bum,

44:43.845 --> 44:45.403
ba-bum, ba-bum, ba-bum,

44:45.480 --> 44:46.811
ba-bum, ba-bum.

44:48.182 --> 44:49.649
Really fast.

44:52.920 --> 44:53.852
I don't understand.

44:53.921 --> 44:55.252
I have been telling you for weeks

44:55.323 --> 44:56.381
that the tiles are chipped.

44:56.457 --> 44:57.617
There's no water pressure.

44:57.692 --> 45:00.160
The handles are coming off
of the cabinets.

45:00.228 --> 45:01.923
Now, you don't have a life.
What's the problem?

45:01.996 --> 45:04.692
Can't you-Hey!
I am talking to you.

45:04.766 --> 45:06.893
Hey! Hey!

45:06.968 --> 45:08.526
Mom, your pants.

45:08.603 --> 45:11.333
I can't talk to you
like this, Mrs. August!

45:11.406 --> 45:14.102
Listen, I'm telling you that-

45:14.175 --> 45:16.109
It's not just that
the tile is chipped.

45:16.177 --> 45:17.838
The carpets are filthy.
They're filthy.

45:17.912 --> 45:20.176
I've got a fungus on my foot
from those carpets.

45:20.248 --> 45:21.875
Who was living here before,
a hockey team?

45:21.949 --> 45:24.213
I cannot live like this!

45:24.285 --> 45:25.377
You can't live like this,

45:25.453 --> 45:27.080
but you can live in
an apartment for 6 months

45:27.155 --> 45:28.622
with just a mattress on the floor?

45:28.690 --> 45:31.124
Ohh!

45:31.192 --> 45:32.625
Damn it!

45:37.432 --> 45:38.660
Ohh!

45:41.302 --> 45:43.566
Turn it down!

45:43.638 --> 45:44.764
God, I hate this place!

45:44.839 --> 45:47.933
I hate my job!
I hate my foot!

45:48.009 --> 45:48.941
Uhh!

46:01.656 --> 46:03.521
You're not having sex
with anybody, are you?

46:06.094 --> 46:07.026
What?

46:07.095 --> 46:09.154
You know.

46:09.230 --> 46:11.164
No, I don't know.

46:18.740 --> 46:20.071
We have to get out of here.

46:20.141 --> 46:21.938
We can't.
We have a lease.

46:22.009 --> 46:26.946
What do you mean,
am I having sex with anyone?

46:36.855 --> 46:39.323
We moved anyway.

46:39.390 --> 46:41.085
Shh, shh, shh.

46:41.159 --> 46:42.820
Over the next year,

46:42.894 --> 46:44.885
we moved a lot.

46:44.963 --> 46:46.692
We got used to it.

46:46.764 --> 46:47.992
Oh, honey, let me help you.

46:48.066 --> 46:49.090
Here.

46:49.167 --> 46:51.135
That's a girl. Ok.
It's apartment number 8?

46:51.202 --> 46:53.136
Yeah, number 8. Ohh.

46:53.204 --> 46:56.173
At least this one had furniture,
thanks to Miss Letterfine.

46:56.241 --> 46:57.265
Thank you.

46:57.342 --> 46:58.468
Thanks.

46:58.543 --> 47:00.340
Gail and Mom
have become good friends.

47:03.348 --> 47:04.280
Cheers.

47:04.349 --> 47:06.283
It's so colorful. Look.

47:06.351 --> 47:08.182
My mom dragged me
to an audition.

47:08.253 --> 47:09.550
- Hello.
- Hi.

47:09.621 --> 47:12.522
She would not give up on her fantasy
of me becoming an actress.

47:12.590 --> 47:15.058
What's your social security number,
sweetheart?

47:15.126 --> 47:16.388
Uh...

47:16.461 --> 47:17.393
Ann?

47:17.462 --> 47:20.295
We did our work

47:20.365 --> 47:21.627
and kept healthy.

47:21.699 --> 47:23.223
And exhale.

47:23.301 --> 47:25.428
Draw your navel
to your backbone.

47:25.503 --> 47:26.800
And when summer came,
we went to the beach

47:26.871 --> 47:29.465
and felt sorry
for everyone back home.

47:29.540 --> 47:30.837
Where are you going?

47:30.909 --> 47:32.137
I think right over there.

47:32.210 --> 47:33.404
There's no people over there.

47:33.478 --> 47:35.946
I know.
I need some peace and quiet today.

47:36.014 --> 47:37.606
You just want to be
near that beach club.

47:37.682 --> 47:39.343
Yes, please.

47:39.417 --> 47:40.975
I'm open.
I'm open.

47:41.052 --> 47:42.542
He's over there.

47:42.620 --> 47:44.087
Yo, Nick.

47:46.858 --> 47:49.122
Here's a good spot.

47:49.193 --> 47:50.319
There you go.

47:50.395 --> 47:53.956
You guys feel like playing
some middleman?

47:54.032 --> 47:55.795
Sweetie, you have
a cute little body.

47:55.867 --> 47:57.164
You should show it off more.

47:57.235 --> 47:58.429
You should show off your body.

47:58.503 --> 48:00.801
I plan to, but-
Where are you going?

48:00.872 --> 48:02.100
Japan.

48:02.173 --> 48:03.401
- Heads up.
- Aah!

48:03.474 --> 48:04.964
Sorry about that.

48:06.711 --> 48:08.440
That's ok.

48:15.954 --> 48:18.047
Ooh!

48:18.122 --> 48:19.919
You're strong.

48:22.360 --> 48:23.292
Wild thing.

48:23.361 --> 48:25.829
Hey, Josh, I'm open.

48:27.832 --> 48:28.764
Aw!

49:10.441 --> 49:12.966
Oh, shame on you.

49:16.080 --> 49:17.513
Oh, Ann.

49:17.582 --> 49:18.640
Ann, come here, sweetie.

49:18.716 --> 49:20.343
This is Dr. Spritzer.

49:20.418 --> 49:22.147
This is my daughter Ann.

49:22.220 --> 49:23.778
Ah, a big girl.

49:23.855 --> 49:26.847
Oh, yes.
We're more like sisters.

49:26.924 --> 49:28.323
So, you're the actress, I hear.

49:28.393 --> 49:30.088
Oh, no, not me. Her.
My mom's the actress.

49:30.161 --> 49:32.061
Oh, silly girl.
Don't be shy.

49:32.130 --> 49:33.961
Dr. Spritzer's an orthodontist,

49:34.032 --> 49:35.556
and he works with the actresses.

49:35.633 --> 49:37.100
He did Heather Locklear.

49:37.168 --> 49:39.033
Her teeth.

49:39.103 --> 49:41.367
I was telling the doctor
that just this morning,

49:41.439 --> 49:42.872
we were discussing your overbite.

49:42.940 --> 49:44.464
See what a great smile she has?

49:44.542 --> 49:46.373
The bottom is just
a little strange.

49:46.444 --> 49:48.105
They don't look
so strange to me.

49:48.179 --> 49:49.111
Josh!

49:49.180 --> 49:50.408
Come on!

49:50.481 --> 49:51.413
Ahem.

49:51.482 --> 49:52.642
Be right there.

49:52.717 --> 49:53.649
Adele.

49:53.718 --> 49:54.980
Yes, Josh.

49:55.053 --> 49:55.985
You play good ball.

49:56.054 --> 49:58.147
You, too.

49:58.222 --> 49:59.348
Take care of those two-fers, now.

49:59.424 --> 50:00.982
An actress has to keep smiling.

50:01.059 --> 50:04.093
See you.

50:07.031 --> 50:09.499
That's probably his wife.

50:09.567 --> 50:11.762
Why'd you have to talk
about my teeth?

50:11.836 --> 50:13.064
It won't last long.

50:13.204 --> 50:14.933
Mom?

50:15.006 --> 50:16.667
- Mom? Mom?
- Ann?

50:16.741 --> 50:17.901
- Mom, guess what.
- What?

50:17.975 --> 50:18.907
Benny's coming.

50:18.976 --> 50:19.908
Yes!

50:19.977 --> 50:21.501
Ohh!

