01:08:16.928 --> 01:08:18.327
Jimmy, don't.

01:08:18.397 --> 01:08:19.328
I'm sorry, Reverend.

01:08:19.398 --> 01:08:21.229
Maybe we should, um, start dinner.

01:08:21.299 --> 01:08:23.529
Sit down, Sylvia.
I'm gonna barbecue.

01:08:23.602 --> 01:08:25.569
Then why don't you start it, honey?

01:08:25.636 --> 01:08:28.367
My uncle Jimmy
was ready to explode.

01:08:29.640 --> 01:08:31.666
I could feel it coming.

01:08:31.743 --> 01:08:33.210
So, Adele...

01:08:33.278 --> 01:08:35.872
do you like California?

01:08:35.947 --> 01:08:38.313
Oh, yeah. Very much.

01:08:38.383 --> 01:08:41.045
What's your day like,
Adele, back there?

01:08:41.118 --> 01:08:42.108
Hal.

01:08:42.187 --> 01:08:43.551
Well, I, uh...

01:08:43.622 --> 01:08:46.648
work a full day at school
with my students.

01:08:46.725 --> 01:08:48.317
And, uh, we live in Beverly Hills,

01:08:48.393 --> 01:08:49.689
so it's quite a commute.

01:08:49.761 --> 01:08:52.252
I have to be in the car
for at least 2 hours.

01:08:52.330 --> 01:08:54.924
Let me tell you something,
Adele, we all work.

01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:55.932
That wasn't necessary.

01:08:56.001 --> 01:08:56.933
Anyone want another drink?

01:08:57.002 --> 01:08:58.332
Jim.

01:08:58.403 --> 01:08:59.995
Of course you work, Jimmy,

01:09:00.071 --> 01:09:04.064
but you've also got
Mom's house now and the RV.

01:09:04.142 --> 01:09:06.372
Could we not have
any fighting today?

01:09:06.444 --> 01:09:08.537
Your life is not
that difficult, is it?

01:09:08.613 --> 01:09:12.412
Well, maybe if I had
had half the help from the family

01:09:12.484 --> 01:09:14.314
that you were lucky enough
to come into, Jimmy.

01:09:14.386 --> 01:09:15.353
You come here a second with me.

01:09:15.420 --> 01:09:16.785
I wanna show you something, Adele.

01:09:16.854 --> 01:09:18.412
You don't have to
talk to her like that.

01:09:18.490 --> 01:09:19.616
I want to show you the deed

01:09:19.691 --> 01:09:20.850
and the mortgage to the house

01:09:20.926 --> 01:09:22.587
that I've been paying on,
that I'm still paying on!

01:09:22.661 --> 01:09:23.593
Damn it, get out of the house.

01:09:23.662 --> 01:09:24.594
You know who helped me

01:09:24.662 --> 01:09:26.596
when I was by myself with a child,

01:09:26.665 --> 01:09:28.359
all by myself?
Nobody.

01:09:28.433 --> 01:09:29.593
Nobody helped me, Jimmy.

01:09:29.667 --> 01:09:31.225
I'm gonna show you the deed.

01:09:31.303 --> 01:09:32.997
You take a look at it.
Either you look at it

01:09:33.071 --> 01:09:34.368
oryou shut your damn mouth
from now on.

01:09:34.439 --> 01:09:36.770
Nobody talks to me like that,
Jimmy, not even you.

01:09:36.841 --> 01:09:39.174
Come on, Ted,
take me to the Holiday Inn.

01:09:39.243 --> 01:09:40.609
Make your phone calls there,
too, not here.

01:09:40.679 --> 01:09:42.374
I knowyou need to get laid
back in Beverly Hills,

01:09:42.447 --> 01:09:44.846
but can't you hold off
a little bit-

01:09:45.917 --> 01:09:47.975
Adele. Adele!

01:09:48.053 --> 01:09:50.020
Your sister's boy is dead.

01:09:50.087 --> 01:09:51.282
Please, everyone just stop this.

01:09:51.356 --> 01:09:53.187
God damn it.

01:09:53.258 --> 01:09:55.021
Back off.

01:09:55.093 --> 01:09:56.219
Come on.
We're going.

01:09:56.294 --> 01:09:58.524
Ann.

01:09:58.597 --> 01:09:59.859
We're going!

01:09:59.931 --> 01:10:02.661
You can stay here
if you want, honey.

01:10:02.734 --> 01:10:04.998
I'll make up Benny's bed for you.

01:10:05.070 --> 01:10:07.334
Benny would love that.

01:10:07.405 --> 01:10:10.033
Ann.

01:11:22.681 --> 01:11:24.148
Not again, mother.

01:11:29.254 --> 01:11:30.744
Get me the telephone.

01:11:30.822 --> 01:11:33.916
Get it yourself,
if you even paid the bill.

01:11:35.493 --> 01:11:37.757
Please hand me the phone.

01:11:37.829 --> 01:11:39.558
He doesn't want to talk
to you anymore.

01:11:39.631 --> 01:11:41.064
Don't you get it, mother?

01:11:50.709 --> 01:11:52.142
Aw.

01:11:52.210 --> 01:11:53.802
Jesus Christ.

01:11:56.982 --> 01:11:58.244
Ready?

01:12:13.098 --> 01:12:16.625
You gotta scrape me from the floor

01:12:16.701 --> 01:12:20.137
Everything around me is changing

01:12:23.041 --> 01:12:25.271
Mom? Rise and shine.

01:12:25.343 --> 01:12:26.970
It's time to get up.

01:12:27.045 --> 01:12:29.445
It's 7... 7:40, Mom.

01:12:29.514 --> 01:12:32.176
I have to get to school.
You have to get to work.

01:12:32.250 --> 01:12:33.217
Come on.

01:12:33.284 --> 01:12:34.979
You have to get out of bed, Mom.

01:12:35.053 --> 01:12:36.247
You've been in bed all weekend.

01:12:36.321 --> 01:12:37.583
You can't do this.

01:12:39.090 --> 01:12:41.456
Ok. I'll drive.
I can drive.

01:12:43.728 --> 01:12:45.855
Get your big ass out of bed!

01:12:45.930 --> 01:12:49.627
But isn't this always what I wanted?

01:12:49.701 --> 01:12:52.727
Isn't it just what I always wanted?

01:12:52.804 --> 01:12:53.930
Go away.

01:13:36.081 --> 01:13:37.446
Hey, Adele.

01:13:40.518 --> 01:13:42.918
George, this is your chance!

01:13:42.987 --> 01:13:45.142
Put down the sign and go. Go.

01:13:45.276 --> 01:13:47.335
Go paint a dam somewhere!

01:13:49.580 --> 01:14:04.987
No money, no work!

01:14:11.235 --> 01:14:13.169
Ah, girls.

01:14:13.237 --> 01:14:15.034
- Hi.
- Hi, Miss August.

01:14:15.105 --> 01:14:17.232
Hi.

01:14:17.308 --> 01:14:18.297
You went shopping?

01:14:18.375 --> 01:14:19.842
I thought you had to
picket or something.

01:14:19.910 --> 01:14:21.810
I can't work at that school.

01:14:21.879 --> 01:14:23.403
I resigned.

01:14:23.480 --> 01:14:25.414
I'm a woman of leisure now.

01:14:25.482 --> 01:14:27.143
Let's celebrate.

01:14:27.218 --> 01:14:29.152
You can't quit.
We won't have any money.

01:14:29.220 --> 01:14:32.451
Honey, they did not pay me
enough to carry a sign.

01:14:32.523 --> 01:14:35.151
That's why you carry
the sign, isn't it?

01:14:35.226 --> 01:14:38.024
You get more money
if you carry the sign.

01:14:41.198 --> 01:14:42.426
No.

01:14:42.499 --> 01:14:44.763
They carry the sign because...

01:14:44.835 --> 01:14:47.599
they like to struggle.

01:14:47.671 --> 01:14:49.935
Some people need to struggle.

01:14:50.007 --> 01:14:50.974
Struggle, struggle, struggle-

01:14:51.041 --> 01:14:52.065
That's what someone taught them.

01:14:52.142 --> 01:14:53.074
Get out there and struggle-

01:14:53.143 --> 01:14:55.077
That's what somebody said to them.

01:14:55.145 --> 01:14:58.911
But we... did not come
to Beverly Hills to struggle.

01:15:02.486 --> 01:15:04.386
We need to pay the rent.

01:15:04.455 --> 01:15:05.820
Yup, that's true.

01:15:05.889 --> 01:15:07.857
So maybe you're just gonna have
to get a little after-school job

01:15:07.925 --> 01:15:09.222
instead of bringing the gals home

01:15:09.293 --> 01:15:10.920
to do their nails all afternoon.

01:15:10.995 --> 01:15:12.485
We're studying for a French test.

01:15:12.563 --> 01:15:14.053
Oh.

01:15:14.131 --> 01:15:16.395
And you shouldn't have quit your job.

01:15:22.706 --> 01:15:25.869
- I am your mother, am I not?
- I guess so.

01:15:25.943 --> 01:15:28.343
Well... ta mère has something

01:15:28.412 --> 01:15:31.438
she would like to say to you en anglais,

01:15:31.515 --> 01:15:32.573
"Auditions.

01:15:32.650 --> 01:15:36.746
Caucasian, female. 12-16.

01:15:36.820 --> 01:15:39.948
Hostile, withdrawn loner."

01:15:40.024 --> 01:15:41.787
You can handle that,
can't you, baby?

01:15:41.859 --> 01:15:43.690
Why are you doing this?

01:15:43.761 --> 01:15:46.992
You could do a little scene from
Terms of Endearment

01:15:47.064 --> 01:15:48.861
or Clueless!

01:15:48.932 --> 01:15:50.092
Yeah.

01:15:50.167 --> 01:15:52.499
I bet you all could
do a scene from Clueless,

01:15:52.569 --> 01:15:53.797
like totally!

01:15:53.871 --> 01:15:55.202
That would be cool.

01:15:56.707 --> 01:15:58.334
I don't know those scenes.

01:15:58.409 --> 01:15:59.933
I don't want to be an actress.

01:16:00.010 --> 01:16:01.671
I don't know how to act.
I don't know anything.

01:16:01.745 --> 01:16:02.871
I don't know why I'm here

01:16:02.946 --> 01:16:03.970
and neither do you.

01:16:04.048 --> 01:16:05.777
And what would you
have rather done,

01:16:05.849 --> 01:16:07.840
stayed back home
and been one of those little girls

01:16:07.918 --> 01:16:09.647
who sits longer
than the others on the porch

01:16:09.720 --> 01:16:13.212
straining to hear the sounds
of the trucks on the highway?

01:16:13.290 --> 01:16:14.780
You're acting crazy again.

01:16:14.858 --> 01:16:15.825
One of those little girls

01:16:15.893 --> 01:16:17.588
who has the names
of cities in her head

01:16:17.661 --> 01:16:19.026
but has never been to one?

01:16:19.096 --> 01:16:21.326
Who dreams of hotels
and has never sat in a lobby?

01:16:21.398 --> 01:16:22.956
Is that what you want?

01:16:23.033 --> 01:16:24.933
Ann, we're gonna go.

01:16:25.002 --> 01:16:25.969
Where are you going?

01:16:26.036 --> 01:16:27.094
I'll see you later, ok?

01:16:27.171 --> 01:16:28.399
I'll call you, Ann.

01:16:28.472 --> 01:16:29.404
Bye, Miss August.

01:16:29.473 --> 01:16:30.701
Call me.

01:16:30.774 --> 01:16:32.241
Ciao.

01:16:39.883 --> 01:16:41.043
All right.

01:16:42.586 --> 01:16:45.248
Where, where is it?
Where do you want me to go?

01:16:45.322 --> 01:16:47.313
All right.

01:16:48.659 --> 01:16:51.287
Circled it for you,
and I can call them for you.

01:16:51.362 --> 01:16:53.592
I'll do it myself.

01:16:53.664 --> 01:16:56.565
They're gonna want you
to do some improv,

01:16:56.633 --> 01:16:59.625
but it should be related
to the material, ok?

01:16:59.703 --> 01:17:00.795
Ok.

01:17:00.871 --> 01:17:01.735
Yes?

01:17:01.805 --> 01:17:02.737
- Hello.
- Hi.

01:17:02.806 --> 01:17:04.740
I'm Heather Ann August's mother.

01:17:04.808 --> 01:17:05.934
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:17:06.009 --> 01:17:07.874
So, um, has she finished her audition?

01:17:07.945 --> 01:17:09.207
Oh, she's in there now.

01:17:09.279 --> 01:17:10.644
- She is?
- Yeah.

01:17:10.714 --> 01:17:12.944
Can I see?
Can I watch her?

01:17:13.016 --> 01:17:14.813
No. We can't interrupt.

01:17:14.885 --> 01:17:16.409
Just a little, tiny bit.

01:17:16.487 --> 01:17:17.613
Uh, excuse me?

01:17:17.688 --> 01:17:20.213
She'd really like
for me to watch.

01:17:20.290 --> 01:17:22.190
I'd rather you didn't.

01:17:22.259 --> 01:17:23.726
- Ok.
- Ok.

01:17:23.794 --> 01:17:24.852
Thanks.

01:17:24.928 --> 01:17:26.418
I need Karen.

01:17:28.665 --> 01:17:29.791
Karen?

01:17:31.001 --> 01:17:31.933
Karen?

01:17:33.871 --> 01:17:35.805
Karen Scarborough?

01:17:36.874 --> 01:17:40.666
Mmm.

01:17:40.744 --> 01:17:42.575
What a man.

01:17:42.646 --> 01:17:45.945
What a meal he made of me

01:17:46.016 --> 01:17:50.077
during that thing
that adults do in bed.

01:17:50.154 --> 01:17:54.784
Not many men know
how to do it, but...

01:17:54.858 --> 01:17:57.088
when they do it...

01:17:57.161 --> 01:17:58.321
it means they...

01:17:58.395 --> 01:18:00.386
really love you.

01:18:01.865 --> 01:18:05.164
They wouldn't just
do it to any woman.

01:18:05.235 --> 01:18:08.398
It means they'll buy you a big house

01:18:08.472 --> 01:18:10.531
with blue shutters and...

01:18:10.607 --> 01:18:12.871
make life easy for you.

01:18:12.943 --> 01:18:17.846
He's going to take us
to the Music Center.

01:18:17.915 --> 01:18:19.439
The opera.

01:18:19.516 --> 01:18:20.778
I love the opera.

01:18:27.791 --> 01:18:30.055
He never returned my call.

01:18:31.295 --> 01:18:34.059
I didn't understand.

01:18:34.131 --> 01:18:36.861
Oh, God, life is so shitty.

01:18:36.934 --> 01:18:39.494
The whole world is so shitty.

01:18:56.019 --> 01:18:57.714
Beverly Hills, what a bummer.

01:19:03.327 --> 01:19:04.453
But...

01:19:06.230 --> 01:19:07.720
so what?

01:19:09.666 --> 01:19:12.829
Like my daddy always used to say...

01:19:12.903 --> 01:19:15.371
Be optimistic

01:19:15.439 --> 01:19:17.566
Don't you be a grumpy

01:19:17.641 --> 01:19:18.835
When the road gets bumpy

01:19:18.909 --> 01:19:21.377
Just smile, smile, smile
and be happy

01:19:21.445 --> 01:19:22.878
Don't wear a long face

01:19:22.946 --> 01:19:25.210
It's never in style

01:19:25.282 --> 01:19:27.750
Be optimistic and smile

01:19:38.996 --> 01:19:42.525
Mom?

01:19:42.599 --> 01:19:45.534
I'm sorry,
but you have to understand

01:19:45.602 --> 01:19:47.001
I was just doing an audition.

01:19:47.070 --> 01:19:50.005
It just came out.
I didn't plan it.

01:19:50.073 --> 01:19:52.667
I didn't do it to hurt
your feelings.

01:20:01.051 --> 01:20:02.746
You weren't supposed to be there.

01:20:02.819 --> 01:20:04.184
I told you not to come.

01:20:07.824 --> 01:20:09.815
I didn't even want
to go to the audition.

01:20:11.995 --> 01:20:14.987
You embarrassed me
in front of my friends.

01:20:17.801 --> 01:20:19.769
I don't know what to say.

01:20:20.837 --> 01:20:22.771
It just-It just happened.

01:20:24.274 --> 01:20:26.538
They wanted me to-

01:20:26.610 --> 01:20:29.511
Nobody would even know it was you.

01:20:36.053 --> 01:20:39.022
I wake up and I don't
even want to be here.

01:20:39.089 --> 01:20:41.057
Who would want to be with you?

01:20:41.124 --> 01:20:43.558
You're just a crazy, middle-aged,

01:20:43.627 --> 01:20:45.390
unemployed school teacher

01:20:45.462 --> 01:20:48.761
with-with a child to support.

01:20:51.335 --> 01:20:53.929
Why can't our lives just be normal?

01:20:57.240 --> 01:21:00.641
You know, I get so scared sometimes

01:21:00.711 --> 01:21:02.679
I want to go find my father.

01:21:07.884 --> 01:21:09.818
You should find your father.

01:21:12.389 --> 01:21:14.482
Maybe he can give you a normal life.

01:21:28.939 --> 01:21:32.431
Hi, Miss Letterfine?
It's Ann August.

01:21:32.509 --> 01:21:34.238
I'm all right.

01:21:34.311 --> 01:21:36.404
Um...

01:21:36.480 --> 01:21:38.243
I'm sorry to disturb you so late,

01:21:38.315 --> 01:21:42.115
but is my mom there?

01:21:44.855 --> 01:21:45.879
Oh.

01:21:47.057 --> 01:21:50.424
No. I...

01:21:50.494 --> 01:21:53.429
Well, she left a little while ago

01:21:53.497 --> 01:21:56.057
and I was just wondering.

01:21:57.567 --> 01:21:58.864
Never mind.

01:22:03.240 --> 01:22:05.174
I'm so sorry to bother you.

01:22:06.877 --> 01:22:08.276
All right.

01:22:10.080 --> 01:22:11.411
Bye.

01:22:52.014 --> 01:22:54.244
We didn't speak.

01:22:59.154 --> 01:23:01.679
We've never
spoken about that day.

01:23:09.631 --> 01:23:12.065
Now my mother was trying
to cover up her feelings

01:23:12.134 --> 01:23:13.897
with orange paint.

01:23:21.243 --> 01:23:23.177
I felt so alone.

01:23:25.380 --> 01:23:26.972
I miss Grandma.

01:23:28.250 --> 01:23:29.717
I miss Benny.

01:23:32.154 --> 01:23:34.384
I never stop missing Benny.

01:23:46.201 --> 01:23:47.566
Go on. Just call.

01:23:47.636 --> 01:23:48.898
You know you want to.

01:23:48.971 --> 01:23:50.165
You've had his number forever.

01:23:50.238 --> 01:23:52.433
You have a perfect right
to call your own dad.

01:23:52.507 --> 01:23:53.974
I bet he's a really nice person

01:23:54.042 --> 01:23:55.475
and just feels guilty

01:23:55.544 --> 01:23:57.273
and hasn't had the nerve
to contact you.

01:23:57.346 --> 01:23:58.813
Do something.

01:23:58.880 --> 01:24:00.814
After all,
he did give you that rabbit's foot

01:24:00.882 --> 01:24:02.440
to remember him by.

01:24:02.517 --> 01:24:03.984
I'll do it.

01:24:04.052 --> 01:24:04.984
No.

01:24:05.053 --> 01:24:06.384
It's ok.

01:24:06.455 --> 01:24:08.548
I'll dial and you talk, ok?

01:24:08.623 --> 01:24:10.557
Ann, just get it over with.

01:24:10.625 --> 01:24:11.592
Don't worry.

01:24:11.660 --> 01:24:13.093
It's gonna be ok.

01:24:14.896 --> 01:24:16.386
I'm sorry.

01:24:17.799 --> 01:24:19.357
It's ringing.
Don't hang up.

01:24:19.434 --> 01:24:21.231
Don't hang up!
Ann!

01:24:21.303 --> 01:24:23.271
Don't hang up.

01:24:26.541 --> 01:24:27.803
Hello?

01:24:30.145 --> 01:24:31.806
Hello?

01:24:31.880 --> 01:24:33.245
Mr. Badir?

01:24:33.315 --> 01:24:35.112
Yes?

01:24:35.183 --> 01:24:39.244
Is this - Is this Hisham Badir?

01:24:39.321 --> 01:24:42.586
Yes. Who is this?

01:24:43.725 --> 01:24:45.317
This is Ann.

01:24:45.394 --> 01:24:48.124
I'm sorry?

01:24:48.196 --> 01:24:50.528
Your daughter Ann.

01:24:54.336 --> 01:24:55.394
Hello?

01:24:55.470 --> 01:24:57.995
Wow. Ann.

01:24:58.073 --> 01:25:01.338
How are you?

01:25:01.410 --> 01:25:05.005
I'm ok.
A little taken by surprise.

01:25:05.080 --> 01:25:07.708
I'd really like to see you.

01:25:07.783 --> 01:25:09.683
Ohh...

01:25:09.751 --> 01:25:11.241
Dad?

01:25:11.319 --> 01:25:13.446
I wasn't exactly ready for this.

01:25:13.522 --> 01:25:15.080
Do you think I could see you?

01:25:18.460 --> 01:25:19.893
I heard you were married again.

01:25:19.961 --> 01:25:21.258
Where did you hear that?

01:25:21.329 --> 01:25:26.062
Someone in Bay City
told Uncle Jimmy.

01:25:26.134 --> 01:25:28.830
Do you have any children?

01:25:28.904 --> 01:25:32.897
Yes. A daughter.

01:25:38.046 --> 01:25:39.638
I have a sister?

01:25:42.751 --> 01:25:45.015
What's her name?

01:25:45.087 --> 01:25:46.577
Tamara.

01:25:46.655 --> 01:25:48.987
She's - She's 9.

01:25:53.361 --> 01:25:57.127
So, uh...

01:25:57.199 --> 01:25:59.030
Does Tamara know about me?

01:26:01.570 --> 01:26:03.197
Do you ever think about me?

01:26:03.271 --> 01:26:05.569
Ann...

01:26:05.640 --> 01:26:07.767
do you need me to
help out in some way?

01:26:11.279 --> 01:26:12.576
What?

01:26:12.647 --> 01:26:14.274
Do you need some money?

01:26:16.485 --> 01:26:18.885
That's - That's a terrible thing to say.

01:26:18.954 --> 01:26:22.947
I - I just wanted to talk to you.

01:26:23.024 --> 01:26:26.152
You're my father, and...

01:26:26.228 --> 01:26:28.219
I thought maybe I could see you.

01:26:28.296 --> 01:26:30.287
I thought perhaps
your mother asked you to.

01:26:30.365 --> 01:26:33.232
My mother didn't ask me
to do anything.

01:26:33.301 --> 01:26:34.598
Why would you say that?

01:26:34.669 --> 01:26:37.160
You know your mother.

01:26:37.239 --> 01:26:40.436
Yes, I do know my mother,
and this isn't about your money.

01:26:40.509 --> 01:26:43.808
She has nothing to do with this.

01:26:43.879 --> 01:26:45.710
Ann...

01:26:45.780 --> 01:26:48.214
I don't know what to say.

01:26:48.283 --> 01:26:52.083
Look, I'm in the middle of something.

01:26:52.154 --> 01:26:54.088
- Can I-
- You don't-

01:26:54.156 --> 01:26:57.853
You're not even glad
that I called, are you?

01:26:57.926 --> 01:27:01.020
You don't care if
you ever see me again.

01:27:01.096 --> 01:27:03.394
You don't give a damn
about me, do you?

01:27:03.465 --> 01:27:06.229
Why don't you give me your number?

01:27:06.301 --> 01:27:07.791
I'm sorry I called you.

01:27:07.869 --> 01:27:10.394
Listen, Ann-

01:27:11.940 --> 01:27:13.373
You're better off without him.

01:27:13.441 --> 01:27:14.840
Write him off.
Who needs him?

01:27:14.910 --> 01:27:17.504
Sue the bastard for
child support or something.

01:27:34.396 --> 01:27:35.920
Hello?

01:27:39.401 --> 01:27:40.333
Hello?

01:27:40.402 --> 01:27:42.233
Ann?

01:27:42.304 --> 01:27:43.566
Yeah, Peter?

01:27:46.074 --> 01:27:48.838
I want to kiss your lips.

01:27:48.910 --> 01:27:50.207
What for?

01:27:52.714 --> 01:27:54.306
I don't know.

01:27:54.382 --> 01:27:57.215
Well, if you can't think of
a better reason than that...

01:28:10.699 --> 01:28:11.631
What?

01:28:11.700 --> 01:28:13.634
I thought of another reason.

01:28:16.338 --> 01:28:19.603
I'm wild about your warm lips

01:28:19.674 --> 01:28:21.608
and I want to squeeze-

01:28:21.676 --> 01:28:24.702
I want to squeeze you tight.

01:28:24.779 --> 01:28:27.077
I want to be one with you.

01:28:27.148 --> 01:28:28.206
Yeah.

01:28:29.618 --> 01:28:33.782
I want to part your lips
with my tongue.

01:28:33.855 --> 01:28:35.880
Yeah, and then what?

01:28:35.957 --> 01:28:37.185
Tell me. Then what?

01:28:39.527 --> 01:28:42.325
I don't know.

01:28:42.397 --> 01:28:44.763
Well, come on over.

01:29:00.081 --> 01:29:01.275
Is your mom home?

01:29:01.349 --> 01:29:02.873
No.

01:29:05.120 --> 01:29:06.246
So...

01:29:09.291 --> 01:29:11.953
Maybe we should go out some night.

01:29:12.027 --> 01:29:13.289
No.

01:29:15.897 --> 01:29:17.956
Come in.

01:29:27.642 --> 01:29:29.075
So, what about that stuff

01:29:29.144 --> 01:29:31.112
you were saying on the phone?

01:29:31.179 --> 01:29:32.646
Where'd you learn that?

01:29:32.714 --> 01:29:34.705
It's just in a book.

01:29:34.783 --> 01:29:37.684
Why don't you take off
your clothes?

01:29:41.289 --> 01:29:42.756
All right. Um...

01:29:45.026 --> 01:29:47.324
Don't you want to talk first?

01:29:47.395 --> 01:29:49.590
It's not even dark outside.

01:29:49.664 --> 01:29:50.722
So?

01:29:56.338 --> 01:29:58.203
Music? Do you want
to put on some music?

01:29:59.407 --> 01:30:00.669
All right.

01:30:52.660 --> 01:30:55.390
Are those initials
on your underwear?

01:30:57.799 --> 01:31:00.199
Yeah. My mom has that done.

01:31:00.268 --> 01:31:02.031
Initial freak.

01:31:03.805 --> 01:31:06.137
Take them off
and bring them to me.

01:31:11.279 --> 01:31:12.871
I want to kiss you.

01:31:15.383 --> 01:31:18.484
Ok.

01:31:39.707 --> 01:31:41.106
Wow.

01:31:57.258 --> 01:31:59.658
That summer I turned 17...

01:32:01.596 --> 01:32:03.564
and I started planning my escape.

01:32:06.234 --> 01:32:08.668
My mother finally found
a job she liked

01:32:08.736 --> 01:32:10.363
at a convalescent home.

01:32:10.438 --> 01:32:12.372
She was good at what she did.

01:32:12.440 --> 01:32:13.429
Here, look at yourself.

01:32:13.508 --> 01:32:16.136
At last she had
a captive audience.

01:32:16.211 --> 01:32:17.974
That was a good one.
Good. Good.

01:32:18.046 --> 01:32:20.674
Waltz.

01:32:20.748 --> 01:32:23.148
And where's that tongue
going on the "I"?

01:32:23.218 --> 01:32:24.150
Waltz.

01:32:24.219 --> 01:32:25.709
It would help if we had

01:32:25.787 --> 01:32:27.254
a little bit snazzier
lipstick here, Jack.

01:32:27.322 --> 01:32:28.812
Ha ha ha!

01:32:28.890 --> 01:32:30.824
Ok, Jack? We gotta get her
some perky lipstick.

01:32:30.892 --> 01:32:33.759
Make that pucker.
Let's try it again.

01:32:33.828 --> 01:32:36.058
"Wuh."

01:32:36.130 --> 01:32:38.325
Waltz.

01:32:39.434 --> 01:32:41.868
I appreciate
how you are with my mother.

01:32:41.936 --> 01:32:43.096
How you are with everybody.

01:32:43.171 --> 01:32:44.900
She's coming along all right.

01:32:44.973 --> 01:32:47.737
I'd like to talk more about this.
After work?

01:32:47.809 --> 01:32:49.777
I could take you out to
lunch or dinner some time?

01:32:49.844 --> 01:32:51.072
Uh, thanks.

01:32:51.145 --> 01:32:52.806
Tell you all about
the carpet business.

01:32:52.881 --> 01:32:53.973
Yeah, sometime.

01:32:55.750 --> 01:32:57.240
Bye, guys.
Bye, Ann.

01:32:57.318 --> 01:32:59.582
Must have bagged
a zillion groceries today.

01:32:59.654 --> 01:33:01.281
You must be so tired.

01:33:01.356 --> 01:33:03.290
I really appreciate
you going with me.

01:33:03.358 --> 01:33:05.417
I just couldn't deal
with it by myself.

01:33:05.493 --> 01:33:07.620
Every time this guy looks
at me and asks me out,

01:33:07.695 --> 01:33:09.663
it's just so sad.

01:33:09.731 --> 01:33:11.961
He's so... nice.

01:33:12.033 --> 01:33:15.264
When my wife died,
I started eating out all the time.

01:33:15.336 --> 01:33:17.361
How was the pot roast?

01:33:17.438 --> 01:33:19.668
Nice. It was nice.

01:33:19.741 --> 01:33:21.470
Think you'll ever
go back to Wisconsin?

01:33:21.543 --> 01:33:24.205
- Not for anything in the world.
- Yeah.

01:33:24.279 --> 01:33:25.940
Well, is it that bad?

01:33:26.014 --> 01:33:28.005
It was a dead end.
That's why we left.

01:33:28.082 --> 01:33:29.515
I sometimes think about

01:33:29.584 --> 01:33:31.814
just picking up and leaving, too.

01:33:31.886 --> 01:33:34.650
Whenever a new shipment
of carpets comes into my store,

01:33:34.722 --> 01:33:37.657
I believe that
somewhere in the pile

01:33:37.725 --> 01:33:39.818
there's one that flies.

01:33:39.894 --> 01:33:42.624
It's been put there for me.

01:33:42.697 --> 01:33:47.066
Some beautifully handwoven
16th century Persian rug

01:33:47.135 --> 01:33:49.194
from A Thousand and One Nights,

01:33:49.270 --> 01:33:50.897
and I sit myself down on it

01:33:50.972 --> 01:33:52.701
and I wave good-bye
to everybody in the store

01:33:52.774 --> 01:33:55.208
and fly right out of the front door.

01:33:55.276 --> 01:33:56.709
When I graduate this year,

01:33:56.778 --> 01:33:58.575
my carpet's gonna fly me
back East to college.

01:33:58.646 --> 01:34:02.013
You better tell your carpet
to drop you at UCLA.

01:34:02.083 --> 01:34:04.176
I'd like to go back East.

01:34:04.252 --> 01:34:05.742
Since when?

01:34:05.820 --> 01:34:08.516
I've been thinking about it.

01:34:08.590 --> 01:34:10.854
Well, independence.
Sounds like her mother.

01:34:10.925 --> 01:34:15.089
She's not going back East.
She's going to UCLA.

01:34:15.163 --> 01:34:16.562
No, I'm not.

01:34:16.631 --> 01:34:19.498
Honey, the hourly wage

01:34:19.567 --> 01:34:21.535
bagging groceries at the supermarket

01:34:21.603 --> 01:34:23.730
is never going to pay
for an eastern college.

01:34:23.805 --> 01:34:26.638
But I'm saving
and I can apply for financial aid

01:34:26.708 --> 01:34:27.675
and Grandma said she'd try to help.

01:34:27.742 --> 01:34:29.369
Your Grandma knows about this?

01:34:29.444 --> 01:34:31.173
She said when the time comes

01:34:31.245 --> 01:34:33.406
maybe she'll be able
to help out a little.

01:34:33.481 --> 01:34:35.449
I'd like to go away to college.

01:34:35.516 --> 01:34:36.448
Why?

01:34:36.517 --> 01:34:37.745
Because I want to get away.

01:34:37.819 --> 01:34:40.151
You wanted to get out
of Bay City, didn't you?

01:34:40.221 --> 01:34:42.052
I want to get out
of Beverly Hills.

01:34:42.123 --> 01:34:43.385
I'm sorry I brought this up.

01:34:43.458 --> 01:34:45.722
You're gonna end up back in Bay City?

01:34:45.793 --> 01:34:46.919
I didn't say that.

01:34:46.995 --> 01:34:48.428
After all this time?

01:34:48.496 --> 01:34:49.963
After all that I've sacrificed?

01:34:50.031 --> 01:34:51.965
Um...

01:34:52.033 --> 01:34:54.558
have you two ever been
down to the grunion run?

01:34:54.636 --> 01:34:58.367
No, Jack.
I have to say we have not been

01:34:58.439 --> 01:35:00.168
to the grunion run.

01:35:00.241 --> 01:35:01.469
What is a grunion?

01:35:01.542 --> 01:35:04.067
It's a little coastal fish.

01:35:04.145 --> 01:35:06.613
It comes up on shore
every once in a while

01:35:06.681 --> 01:35:08.273
during high tide
and lays its eggs in the moonlight.

01:35:08.349 --> 01:35:09.839
And then it dies.

01:35:09.917 --> 01:35:12.351
It's yet another example of a mother

01:35:12.420 --> 01:35:14.411
giving her life for her child.

01:35:14.489 --> 01:35:16.650
Well, some of them die.
Not all of them.

01:35:16.724 --> 01:35:18.919
Sounds really interesting.
I'd love to see that.

01:35:18.993 --> 01:35:20.551
Well, I'd like to take you.

01:35:20.628 --> 01:35:21.822
Great.

01:35:25.667 --> 01:35:27.157
I like him.

01:35:27.235 --> 01:35:29.703
He gets on my nerves.

01:35:29.771 --> 01:35:32.205
He likes you,
and if he asks you out again,

01:35:32.273 --> 01:35:33.535
I hope you'll go.

01:35:33.608 --> 01:35:35.735
He asked me to go to Las Vegas
for the weekend.

01:35:35.810 --> 01:35:38.574
Good. You should go.
You might have fun.

01:35:38.646 --> 01:35:40.079
He is not my type.

01:35:40.148 --> 01:35:42.048
He's not my idea of fun.

01:35:42.116 --> 01:35:45.279
Go to Vegas, Mom.
Take a chance.

01:35:45.353 --> 01:35:47.287
You don't have to fall
in love with him.

01:35:47.355 --> 01:35:48.652
I'm not asking you
to even sleep with him.

01:35:48.723 --> 01:35:50.520
Oh, thank you.

01:35:50.591 --> 01:35:52.456
You could win the jackpot even.

01:35:52.527 --> 01:35:55.018
All right, I will go to Vegas.

01:35:55.096 --> 01:35:57.064
Fine. Just stop it.

01:35:57.131 --> 01:35:58.792
But you are going to UCLA.

01:35:58.866 --> 01:36:01.391
It's a state school,
it's all that we can afford,

01:36:01.469 --> 01:36:04.461
and I do not want to hear
another word about it.

01:36:10.211 --> 01:36:12.907
"Jackpot."

01:36:14.582 --> 01:36:16.015
My mother didn't know it,

01:36:16.084 --> 01:36:18.712
but I'd already applied to
Brown University in Rhode Island.

01:36:18.786 --> 01:36:22.847
Peter tried to talk me
into going to Berkeley,

01:36:22.924 --> 01:36:25.859
but my heart was set
on the East Coast.

01:36:25.927 --> 01:36:27.360
My grades were really good,

01:36:27.428 --> 01:36:30.261
and I thought I could get
a full scholarship.

01:36:30.331 --> 01:36:32.993
I like the part
about the noble soul,

01:36:33.067 --> 01:36:35.467
but do you really read Nietzsche?

01:36:37.371 --> 01:36:38.804
I mean, I read Nietzsche.

01:36:38.873 --> 01:36:40.306
I don't really read Nietzsche.

01:36:42.243 --> 01:36:44.438
He'd be a crazy friend to have,
don't you think?

01:36:44.512 --> 01:36:46.571
Mm-hmm.

01:36:46.647 --> 01:36:49.081
Besides, I think people
who read Nietzsche,

01:36:49.150 --> 01:36:52.051
like really read Nietzsche,
are kinda...

01:36:52.120 --> 01:36:54.588
I don't know.
Kierkegaard, though, he said that-

01:37:34.335 --> 01:37:36.861
Where's the mail?

01:37:36.938 --> 01:37:38.303
Right there.

01:37:41.843 --> 01:37:43.003
You opened it.

01:37:43.077 --> 01:37:44.442
Well, how else am I going to know

01:37:44.512 --> 01:37:46.571
how you're planning your life?

01:37:46.647 --> 01:37:48.945
After all, I'm only your mother.

01:37:49.017 --> 01:37:51.315
Why would you confide in me,
thank you very much.

01:37:51.386 --> 01:37:54.378
Go ahead. Open it.

01:37:54.455 --> 01:37:56.650
I'm sure you'll be very happy.

01:37:59.961 --> 01:38:02.156
Providence, Rhode Island?

01:38:02.230 --> 01:38:05.131
Could you have gotten
any farther away from me?

01:38:07.869 --> 01:38:10.337
Look, I just don't understand.

01:38:10.405 --> 01:38:13.169
After all these years,
after all our hard work,

01:38:13.241 --> 01:38:16.233
would it have killed you
to just stick around a bit

01:38:16.310 --> 01:38:18.141
and show some respect
and appreciation

01:38:18.212 --> 01:38:20.271
to the people that have
worried about you

01:38:20.348 --> 01:38:21.372
and loved you

01:38:21.449 --> 01:38:22.575
and have sacrificed
everything for you?

01:38:22.650 --> 01:38:25.847
I'm not going anywhere!

01:38:25.920 --> 01:38:28.081
If you're going to read my mail,
read it carefully.

01:38:28.156 --> 01:38:31.717
They're giving me some money
for tuition and fees,

01:38:31.793 --> 01:38:33.590
but not all of it,
and we have to pay part of it.

01:38:33.661 --> 01:38:36.289
And we don't have that.

01:38:36.364 --> 01:38:40.164
Read it.
"Parents' contributions."

01:38:40.234 --> 01:38:42.600
God, I wanted it so bad.

01:39:03.491 --> 01:39:06.654
Oh, Pooh Bear,
it's not the end of the world.

01:39:06.727 --> 01:39:09.127
It is the end of the world!

01:39:09.197 --> 01:39:11.563
Maybe not for you,
but it is for me.

01:39:21.843 --> 01:39:23.174
We could get an ice cream.

01:39:23.244 --> 01:39:24.541
No!

01:39:24.612 --> 01:39:28.446
Can't you understand?
I want to go away to college.

01:39:28.516 --> 01:39:31.144
I want to be on my own
and you on your own.

01:39:31.219 --> 01:39:33.653
And I know you're scared
to be without me,

01:39:33.721 --> 01:39:35.586
but I can't help that.

01:39:35.656 --> 01:39:38.216
And I feel bad about that,

01:39:38.292 --> 01:39:41.056
but I don't want
that job anymore.

01:39:41.129 --> 01:39:44.394
Let me live my own life.
Let me go.

01:40:13.528 --> 01:40:15.496
Ohh.

01:40:31.779 --> 01:40:32.803
Good afternoon.

01:40:32.880 --> 01:40:34.711
You went through that
stop sign back there.

01:40:34.782 --> 01:40:37.080
I need your driver's license
and registration, please.

01:40:39.086 --> 01:40:41.486
You want to take
the driver's license

01:40:41.556 --> 01:40:43.251
out of this, please?

01:40:43.324 --> 01:40:44.916
Oh, my God.

01:40:44.992 --> 01:40:46.516
What?

01:40:46.594 --> 01:40:50.428
